1
00:00:12,461 --> 00:00:18,101
(Amid Songdo's forest of skyscrapers)

2
00:00:29,411 --> 00:00:31,541
(Street Beer Festival)

3
00:00:31,841 --> 00:00:34,250
- It's finally here. Bar snacks.
- Bar snacks.

4
00:00:34,251 --> 00:00:37,821
There seems to be a lot of young people.

5
00:00:38,321 --> 00:00:39,991
Spicy and salty.

6
00:00:40,151 --> 00:00:42,720
Surprisingly, street food goes well with beer.

7
00:00:42,721 --> 00:00:44,691
Design, presentation of the food,

8
00:00:44,721 --> 00:00:46,021
and performance.

9
00:00:46,291 --> 00:00:48,591
I will go all out to win...

10
00:00:49,231 --> 00:00:50,731
people's hearts.

11
00:00:51,001 --> 00:00:52,560
(Expected number of visitors)

12
00:00:52,561 --> 00:00:54,501
(2,000 people)

13
00:00:54,571 --> 00:00:56,671
(To provide bar snacks to 2,000 people)

14
00:00:57,341 --> 00:00:59,711
(They leave Sejong.)

15
00:01:01,711 --> 00:01:04,241
(18 vendors arrived in Songdo.)

16
00:01:09,881 --> 00:01:14,451
(The second Street Arena)

17
00:01:15,851 --> 00:01:18,720
(Songdo Moonlight Festival Park in Incheon at 11:30am)

18
00:01:18,721 --> 00:01:19,760
This will be wild.

19
00:01:19,761 --> 00:01:21,291
The prices are written up there.

20
00:01:21,891 --> 00:01:22,891
It will be war.

21
00:01:23,331 --> 00:01:24,961
- The price is eight dollars.
- All right.

22
00:01:26,471 --> 00:01:27,701
- The prices...
- The prices are...

23
00:01:28,171 --> 00:01:30,240
Street Restaurant Fighter.

24
00:01:30,241 --> 00:01:32,941
Welcome to Round Two.

25
00:01:33,841 --> 00:01:34,841
It will be war.

26
00:01:35,211 --> 00:01:36,311
Five dollars.

27
00:01:37,781 --> 00:01:40,151
Food that costs eight dollars. That's ours.

28
00:01:40,551 --> 00:01:43,421
For the 1-on-1 same price battle on Round 2,

29
00:01:43,981 --> 00:01:46,351
two restaurants will go head-to-head...

30
00:01:46,991 --> 00:01:49,321
with the same ingredient budget and the same selling price.

31
00:01:50,021 --> 00:01:53,360
Only one restaurant will survive.

32
00:01:53,361 --> 00:01:55,561
- Half of us are getting eliminated?
- Half are going home.

33
00:01:56,861 --> 00:01:58,630
For Round 2,

34
00:01:58,631 --> 00:02:02,431
menu prices range from 5 dollars to 35 dollars.

35
00:02:02,971 --> 00:02:05,441
There's a total of nine prices.

36
00:02:06,641 --> 00:02:08,270
The price is determined at random.

37
00:02:08,271 --> 00:02:09,271
(The match up price is decided randomly.)

38
00:02:09,272 --> 00:02:10,280
(8 dollars)

39
00:02:10,281 --> 00:02:11,281
(20 dollars)

40
00:02:11,282 --> 00:02:12,410
(35 dollars)

41
00:02:12,411 --> 00:02:14,951
Each match up consists of two rounds,

42
00:02:15,051 --> 00:02:17,251
the 1st half and the 2nd half.

43
00:02:18,251 --> 00:02:21,691
The restaurants must serve a different dish in each half.

44
00:02:22,691 --> 00:02:25,591
The 1st restaurant to earn 2 points is...

45
00:02:25,721 --> 00:02:27,231
guaranteed to survive.

46
00:02:27,791 --> 00:02:30,301
If the match ends in a 1-1 tie,

47
00:02:30,861 --> 00:02:33,670
the winner will be decided by customer ratings.

48
00:02:33,671 --> 00:02:34,931
(Team A loses with 3.2 stars, Team B wins with 4.3 stars)

49
00:02:35,871 --> 00:02:38,201
Each match up receives the same ingredient budget.

50
00:02:38,501 --> 00:02:42,211
Both restaurants can check each other's ingredient costs.

51
00:02:42,511 --> 00:02:45,981
For this round, each restaurant may use...

52
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:48,751
the space in front of its booth if desired.

53
00:02:49,151 --> 00:02:52,580
In Round Two, blind service may be lifted...

54
00:02:52,581 --> 00:02:55,021
if both competing restaurants agree.

55
00:02:55,491 --> 00:02:56,521
I'm confident.

56
00:02:56,921 --> 00:02:58,391
This is a beer festival.

57
00:02:58,721 --> 00:03:00,361
Shouldn't the chefs be out there too?

58
00:03:00,761 --> 00:03:03,960
You can't fully enjoy the festival with blind service, can you?

59
00:03:03,961 --> 00:03:05,031
(Interacting with customers is part of running a restaurant.)

60
00:03:05,061 --> 00:03:07,771
However, Round Two sales are...

61
00:03:08,371 --> 00:03:11,201
adjusted based on customer ratings.

62
00:03:11,971 --> 00:03:12,971
What?

63
00:03:12,972 --> 00:03:14,471
Sales are adjusted based on customer ratings?

64
00:03:14,571 --> 00:03:15,641
What does that mean?

65
00:03:15,741 --> 00:03:17,211
- What?
- All of a sudden?

66
00:03:17,711 --> 00:03:20,381
Average customer ratings of five points equal...

67
00:03:20,651 --> 00:03:22,850
130 percent of the total sales.

68
00:03:22,851 --> 00:03:24,620
(130 percent of total sales)

69
00:03:24,621 --> 00:03:25,721
When you get five points?

70
00:03:26,421 --> 00:03:30,091
Four points equal 110 percent of the total sales.

71
00:03:30,161 --> 00:03:34,061
Three points equal 90 percent of the total sales.

72
00:03:34,791 --> 00:03:36,631
If you get three points, your sales are reduced.

73
00:03:36,661 --> 00:03:38,861
- They get reduced.
- Of course.

74
00:03:39,561 --> 00:03:43,001
Two points equal 70 percent of the total sales.

75
00:03:43,171 --> 00:03:47,610
One point equals 50 percent of the total sales.

76
00:03:47,611 --> 00:03:49,541
That's how the total sales are calculated.

77
00:03:49,641 --> 00:03:51,341
- Fifty percent of your sales?
- Yes.

78
00:03:52,211 --> 00:03:54,211
- That's like losing money.
- Exactly.

79
00:03:54,551 --> 00:03:57,481
Getting one point would be very humiliating.

80
00:03:58,121 --> 00:04:00,290
Quality and an experience that's worth the price must be provided.

81
00:04:00,291 --> 00:04:01,650
Exactly.

82
00:04:01,651 --> 00:04:03,390
Selling a lot isn't the only thing that matters.

83
00:04:03,391 --> 00:04:04,760
- Right.
- The quality is also important?

84
00:04:04,761 --> 00:04:07,130
- The quality is important.
- Customer satisfaction is key.

85
00:04:07,131 --> 00:04:08,430
I'm used to customer ratings.

86
00:04:08,431 --> 00:04:09,490
I agree with it...

87
00:04:09,491 --> 00:04:11,831
because customer reviews affect sales.

88
00:04:11,931 --> 00:04:13,701
- They affect repeat business.
- Right.

89
00:04:14,571 --> 00:04:16,171
Look at that display stand.

90
00:04:16,201 --> 00:04:17,641
What's with Hoon's booth?

91
00:04:18,401 --> 00:04:19,501
What's that?

92
00:04:19,911 --> 00:04:21,570
Did they make that too?

93
00:04:21,571 --> 00:04:23,111
My goodness.

94
00:04:23,141 --> 00:04:24,241
Let's hurry.

95
00:04:24,311 --> 00:04:25,341
It's heavy.

96
00:04:26,751 --> 00:04:28,750
HunGry, what are you guys doing?

97
00:04:28,751 --> 00:04:31,851
- I'll go and kick it.
- What did you bring?

98
00:04:32,421 --> 00:04:34,751
Needless to say, I brought it to win.

99
00:04:34,991 --> 00:04:37,760
People need to notice our booth first...

100
00:04:37,761 --> 00:04:39,760
for them to come over.

101
00:04:39,761 --> 00:04:42,691
I created a display stand in front of the booth.

102
00:04:43,161 --> 00:04:44,830
He's so good.

103
00:04:44,831 --> 00:04:46,530
I didn't even think of that.

104
00:04:46,531 --> 00:04:47,901
How did I not think of that?

105
00:04:48,531 --> 00:04:49,531
Do you need help?

106
00:04:50,041 --> 00:04:52,041
Let's get a shot of everyone helping out.

107
00:04:54,111 --> 00:04:56,411
Gosh, he's so cheerful.

108
00:04:56,881 --> 00:04:59,681
We need to show that there's more than what's on display.

109
00:04:59,911 --> 00:05:03,450
You should concentrate on making food instead.

110
00:05:03,451 --> 00:05:04,451
Are you a carpenter?

111
00:05:05,251 --> 00:05:07,151
No, but I want to try everything I can.

112
00:05:08,821 --> 00:05:10,261
What's that?

113
00:05:10,461 --> 00:05:11,561
It's a food warmer.

114
00:05:12,321 --> 00:05:13,330
Put it here.

115
00:05:13,331 --> 00:05:16,761
The first half of service begins at 5pm.

116
00:05:17,001 --> 00:05:18,731
Please get ready...

117
00:05:19,061 --> 00:05:20,171
- Let's go.
- for the beer festival.

118
00:05:20,571 --> 00:05:22,370
- Let's do this.
- Nothing is ready at all.

119
00:05:22,371 --> 00:05:23,970
(Time before the opening)

120
00:05:23,971 --> 00:05:25,170
Looking forward to working with you.

121
00:05:25,171 --> 00:05:27,111
- Same here.
- Let's do an amazing job.

122
00:05:27,371 --> 00:05:28,810
Let's make it fun.

123
00:05:28,811 --> 00:05:30,680
We're competing, but let's be more like a team.

124
00:05:30,681 --> 00:05:32,280
- We're Team 25 Dollars.
- Exactly.

125
00:05:32,281 --> 00:05:33,281
Let's do that.

126
00:05:33,681 --> 00:05:35,751
Can I call them two masters?

127
00:05:38,821 --> 00:05:41,621
It's amazing to watch two legends facing off.

128
00:05:43,991 --> 00:05:47,360
I learned so much by studying...

129
00:05:47,361 --> 00:05:48,730
their cooking.

130
00:05:48,731 --> 00:05:51,031
It's going to be a huge showdown.

131
00:05:51,301 --> 00:05:52,861
A battle between two masters of French cuisine.

132
00:05:53,001 --> 00:05:55,430
It'll be like watching a classic rivalry, a soccer match...

133
00:05:55,431 --> 00:05:57,201
between England and Spain.

134
00:05:57,741 --> 00:05:58,871
You know what?

135
00:05:59,641 --> 00:06:03,111
I had a feeling that Chef Lim Ki Hak would pick me.

136
00:06:03,441 --> 00:06:04,441
To be honest.

137
00:06:04,811 --> 00:06:08,110
He's a chef who's passionate about preserving...

138
00:06:08,111 --> 00:06:10,121
the roots of French cuisine.

139
00:06:10,781 --> 00:06:13,021
I'm also running a French restaurant myself.

140
00:06:13,251 --> 00:06:16,050
If anything, that makes it even more exciting.

141
00:06:16,051 --> 00:06:19,321
I thought, "It's finally here."

142
00:06:19,391 --> 00:06:22,491
With nothing but respect and admiration.

143
00:06:22,731 --> 00:06:24,500
With respect,

144
00:06:24,501 --> 00:06:26,871
he's challenging him to cross blades.

145
00:06:28,101 --> 00:06:29,530
(25-dollar battle of the French masters)

146
00:06:29,531 --> 00:06:32,070
How will the French cuisine...

147
00:06:32,071 --> 00:06:34,470
win over the market?

148
00:06:34,471 --> 00:06:35,510
(1-on-1 match between 2 culinary legends)

149
00:06:35,511 --> 00:06:37,910
It will be a battle between veterans...

150
00:06:37,911 --> 00:06:40,681
who have been in this industry forever.

151
00:06:41,551 --> 00:06:42,951
Twenty-five dollars.

152
00:06:43,481 --> 00:06:45,621
BOL A BOL versus Ma Restaurant.

153
00:06:46,351 --> 00:06:47,621
They placed second last time.

154
00:06:47,691 --> 00:06:49,291
The high price makes it even more exciting, right?

155
00:06:49,451 --> 00:06:50,461
Chef Lim Ki Hak...

156
00:06:52,591 --> 00:06:53,591
That's amazing.

157
00:06:54,531 --> 00:06:56,031
Chef Lim is truly amazing.

158
00:06:56,561 --> 00:06:57,800
That's just like him.

159
00:06:57,801 --> 00:06:58,831
(Lyon's charcuterie platter)

160
00:07:01,071 --> 00:07:02,471
Charcuterie platter.

161
00:07:02,931 --> 00:07:04,401
Charcuterie platter?

162
00:07:05,171 --> 00:07:08,311
(The name alone gets everyone talking.)

163
00:07:08,511 --> 00:07:09,811
I have to give him credit.

164
00:07:09,871 --> 00:07:11,481
He's planning to make that.

165
00:07:11,611 --> 00:07:13,311
- You'll make that here?
- Yes.

166
00:07:15,451 --> 00:07:17,651
Are you mad or what?

167
00:07:21,121 --> 00:07:24,891
Under the theme "A Trip to France in One Bowl,"

168
00:07:25,221 --> 00:07:28,831
I chose Lyon as the destination for the first half.

169
00:07:29,161 --> 00:07:31,500
(Lyon)

170
00:07:31,501 --> 00:07:34,470
Lyon is a city famous for charcuterie.

171
00:07:34,471 --> 00:07:35,500
(A traditional French dish made by curing, seasoning, or drying meat)

172
00:07:35,501 --> 00:07:37,340
For food to pair with beer,

173
00:07:37,341 --> 00:07:40,270
I thought a charcuterie platter would be perfect.

174
00:07:40,271 --> 00:07:42,341
(Lyon-style charcuterie platter, 25 dollars)

175
00:07:42,811 --> 00:07:44,341
Lyon-style sausage.

176
00:07:45,141 --> 00:07:46,541
Pate en croute.

177
00:07:46,751 --> 00:07:49,910
And roulade. I prepared these three.

178
00:07:49,911 --> 00:07:50,920
(Roulade is made by rolling meat and fillings and slicing thinly.)

179
00:07:50,921 --> 00:07:51,951
(Pate en croute, French-style meat pie eaten cold)

180
00:07:52,851 --> 00:07:54,590
It's a difficult dish that takes at least 2 to 3 days...

181
00:07:54,591 --> 00:07:56,860
including shaping the dough and letting it cool.

182
00:07:56,861 --> 00:07:58,160
(Including shaping the dough and cooling,)

183
00:07:58,161 --> 00:07:59,161
(it takes at least 2 to 3 days.)

184
00:07:59,261 --> 00:08:00,661
Chef, I'm starting the molding.

185
00:08:00,861 --> 00:08:02,691
- What?
- I'm starting to mold.

186
00:08:03,831 --> 00:08:06,061
My goodness.

187
00:08:06,301 --> 00:08:09,130
Pate en croute isn't something...

188
00:08:09,131 --> 00:08:11,801
you can make quickly.

189
00:08:11,941 --> 00:08:14,711
But I wanted to do everything it takes to show people.

190
00:08:15,011 --> 00:08:16,981
Shall I get started?

191
00:08:18,611 --> 00:08:20,911
The meat is cured, ground,

192
00:08:22,381 --> 00:08:26,420
and mixed with dried apricots and pistachios.

193
00:08:26,421 --> 00:08:27,851
(Pate mix: Pork, dried apricots, pistachios)

194
00:08:29,351 --> 00:08:33,391
(The pate mold is coated with butter.)

195
00:08:34,461 --> 00:08:37,801
(Dough: Water, eggs, flour)

196
00:08:38,461 --> 00:08:40,271
The dough is placed in the mold.

197
00:08:41,971 --> 00:08:43,501
(Coating it with egg mixture)

198
00:08:45,441 --> 00:08:48,211
The dough is filled with meat mixture before baking.

199
00:08:51,941 --> 00:08:55,751
(After a long and careful preparation process)

200
00:08:55,851 --> 00:08:56,921
Ta-da.

201
00:08:59,751 --> 00:09:03,620
Normally, you need to let it rest for a full day...

202
00:09:03,621 --> 00:09:06,520
and move it from the mold when it has completely cooled...

203
00:09:06,521 --> 00:09:07,661
and set.

204
00:09:07,891 --> 00:09:10,401
Making this was a challenge even for me.

205
00:09:11,101 --> 00:09:14,000
The key was figuring out...

206
00:09:14,001 --> 00:09:16,601
how to speed up the process.

207
00:09:17,071 --> 00:09:20,141
(Storing in the freezer for a certain amount of time)

208
00:09:20,641 --> 00:09:22,371
I hope I can take it out.

209
00:09:22,911 --> 00:09:23,980
Are you going to remove it now?

210
00:09:23,981 --> 00:09:25,041
Yes, so I can wash it...

211
00:09:25,811 --> 00:09:27,711
I've never taken out pate when it hasn't cooled down.

212
00:09:30,651 --> 00:09:32,381
(A 1st time challenge even for a French chef of 20 years)

213
00:09:32,681 --> 00:09:35,191
(For a clean release from the mold, it's heated one more time.)

214
00:09:36,591 --> 00:09:37,621
Can I get this out?

215
00:09:42,091 --> 00:09:43,731
This is even more challenging.

216
00:09:45,301 --> 00:09:48,101
(Removing the bottom of the mold first)

217
00:09:48,301 --> 00:09:50,471
(It's time to remove each of the side.)

218
00:09:51,341 --> 00:09:52,871
(Grunting)

219
00:09:53,911 --> 00:09:55,941
(He removes one side successfully.)

220
00:09:56,271 --> 00:09:57,481
This side might not come off.

221
00:09:58,041 --> 00:09:59,341
You can't stop now.

222
00:09:59,581 --> 00:10:00,651
You'll make it.

223
00:10:09,051 --> 00:10:10,521
This was a real challenge.

224
00:10:11,091 --> 00:10:12,890
Look at the cross section. It came out beautifully.

225
00:10:12,891 --> 00:10:14,691
Gosh, it looks amazing.

226
00:10:19,661 --> 00:10:21,000
I got the hang of slicing it now.

227
00:10:21,001 --> 00:10:23,201
(Moist and clean-cut interior)

228
00:10:23,331 --> 00:10:24,741
Pate is ready.

229
00:10:26,141 --> 00:10:28,170
Seeing him pull that off on-site made me think,

230
00:10:28,171 --> 00:10:29,411
"That's Chef Lim Ki Hak for you."

231
00:10:30,181 --> 00:10:31,181
I give him credit.

232
00:10:31,911 --> 00:10:33,881
(Chuckling)

233
00:10:34,051 --> 00:10:35,081
I should take a photo.

234
00:10:36,411 --> 00:10:37,581
I can't believe I made it.

235
00:10:38,251 --> 00:10:40,081
I know, in so little time.

236
00:10:41,021 --> 00:10:42,751
- Did you buy that in France?
- Yes.

237
00:10:43,821 --> 00:10:44,890
I'm also preparing the potatoes...

238
00:10:44,891 --> 00:10:45,961
- in a French way.
- Right.

239
00:10:48,461 --> 00:10:51,201
- Gosh, aligot looks great.
- It looks like aligot.

240
00:10:51,301 --> 00:10:52,960
Everyone would love it.

241
00:10:52,961 --> 00:10:54,370
(French-inspired mashed potatoes)

242
00:10:54,371 --> 00:10:55,601
I prepared mashed potatoes...

243
00:10:55,731 --> 00:10:58,441
and carrot rapee to serve on the side.

244
00:10:59,371 --> 00:11:00,510
(Using the same pate mixture)

245
00:11:00,511 --> 00:11:01,940
I used the same ingredients,

246
00:11:01,941 --> 00:11:04,410
but with different shape and cooking method,

247
00:11:04,411 --> 00:11:05,811
I made roulade.

248
00:11:10,921 --> 00:11:12,080
The sausages look amazing.

249
00:11:12,081 --> 00:11:13,451
(Lyon-style sausages filled with charcoal aroma)

250
00:11:13,651 --> 00:11:15,591
While we make a 15-dollar dish,

251
00:11:15,791 --> 00:11:17,420
Chef Lim Ki Hak must be making...

252
00:11:17,421 --> 00:11:20,021
charcuterie calmly and elegantly.

253
00:11:28,831 --> 00:11:30,301
He's intimidating us with sounds.

254
00:11:30,441 --> 00:11:31,441
You're right.

255
00:11:33,711 --> 00:11:35,740
There's no way we'd make sounds like that.

256
00:11:35,741 --> 00:11:36,741
Right.

257
00:11:37,181 --> 00:11:39,811
(Meanwhile, the next-door vendor is busy.)

258
00:11:40,141 --> 00:11:42,881
I couldn't care anything...

259
00:11:43,011 --> 00:11:44,521
about what was happening next door.

260
00:11:45,451 --> 00:11:47,750
I could barely keep up with myself.

261
00:11:47,751 --> 00:11:49,851
How was I supposed to pay attention to anyone else?

262
00:11:50,221 --> 00:11:51,520
- Shrimp?
- It's here.

263
00:11:51,521 --> 00:11:53,561
- Okay.
- I wasn't looking at anyone else.

264
00:11:55,391 --> 00:11:56,591
Shouldn't you grill it?

265
00:11:58,201 --> 00:11:59,830
Chef, what are you making?

