538
00:23:38,161 --> 00:23:40,230
We need to break through by attracting more customers.

539
00:23:40,231 --> 00:23:41,731
To make my booth look more attractive...

540
00:23:42,631 --> 00:23:44,230
- If food is laid out in front, - Hello.

541
00:23:44,231 --> 00:23:46,540
people can see it and consider buying from us.

542
00:23:46,541 --> 00:23:48,110
So I placed butter rice cakes next to the samples.

543
00:23:48,111 --> 00:23:50,271
Cream shrimp and sweet fried chicken comes with a free butter rice cake.

544
00:23:50,541 --> 00:23:52,980
Buy sweet fried chicken and get a butter rice cake for free.

545
00:23:52,981 --> 00:23:55,151
Cream shrimp and sweet fried chicken comes with a free butter rice cake.

546
00:23:55,611 --> 00:23:57,250
Come and have cream shrimp and sweet fried chicken.

547
00:23:57,251 --> 00:23:58,320
We give you a free butter rice cake.

548
00:23:58,321 --> 00:23:59,580
(Cream shrimp and sweet fried chicken)

549
00:23:59,581 --> 00:24:00,721
Come and try it.

550
00:24:01,391 --> 00:24:02,751
It's cream shrimp and sweet fried chicken.

551
00:24:03,621 --> 00:24:04,961
These must be butter rice cakes.

552
00:24:05,721 --> 00:24:07,461
- Have you tried it?
- No, I haven't.

553
00:24:08,391 --> 00:24:09,861
Two butter rice cakes.

554
00:24:10,731 --> 00:24:11,801
- Here.
- Thank you.

555
00:24:13,061 --> 00:24:15,500
The butter rice cakes are on the house. They're hard to find.

556
00:24:15,501 --> 00:24:17,331
Cream shrimp and sweet fried chicken comes with a free butter rice cake.

557
00:24:17,471 --> 00:24:18,740
- Is it tasty?
- Very.

558
00:24:18,741 --> 00:24:21,311
Look at the big portion. It has shrimps and chicken.

559
00:24:21,641 --> 00:24:24,311
(The next customer is on the fence.)

560
00:24:25,711 --> 00:24:26,781
We give you butter rice cakes.

561
00:24:27,611 --> 00:24:29,350
- Welcome.
- Buy sweet fried chicken...

562
00:24:29,351 --> 00:24:30,651
and get a free butter rice cake.

563
00:24:30,881 --> 00:24:32,450
- This is 13 dollars?
- Yes, this is 13 dollars.

564
00:24:32,451 --> 00:24:34,521
- And you get one butter rice cake.
- My gosh.

565
00:24:35,251 --> 00:24:37,220
- Will you confirm the order?
- Buy sweet fried chicken...

566
00:24:37,221 --> 00:24:38,421
and get a free butter rice cake.

567
00:24:38,691 --> 00:24:39,861
Buy-1-get-1-free strategy.

568
00:24:39,921 --> 00:24:41,230
You get a free butter rice cake if you buy sweet fried chicken.

569
00:24:41,231 --> 00:24:43,060
I kept shouting that nonstop.

570
00:24:43,061 --> 00:24:46,201
Many customers came when they heard butter rice cake.

571
00:24:46,361 --> 00:24:48,471
Cream shrimp and sweet fried chicken comes with a free butter rice cake.

572
00:24:48,531 --> 00:24:49,531
(A continuous inflow of customers)

573
00:24:49,532 --> 00:24:50,901
It's delicious. Try it.

574
00:24:51,201 --> 00:24:52,970
- Butter rice cake.
- The queue is long over there,

575
00:24:52,971 --> 00:24:54,041
but you can get our food right away.

576
00:24:54,141 --> 00:24:55,711
This big of a portion for 13 dollars.

577
00:24:56,611 --> 00:24:57,910
- That's such a win.
- It's such a win, right?

578
00:24:57,911 --> 00:24:59,881
That's a huge win. Let's buy it right now.

579
00:25:00,841 --> 00:25:02,680
(Order)

580
00:25:02,681 --> 00:25:04,950
Have beer and sweet fried chicken.

581
00:25:04,951 --> 00:25:06,181
"Free butter rice cake?"

582
00:25:06,821 --> 00:25:08,090
You get a free butter rice cake.

583
00:25:08,091 --> 00:25:09,491
Watch out for the beer.

584
00:25:10,151 --> 00:25:11,390
(A queue has formed.)

585
00:25:11,391 --> 00:25:13,661
Come and have sweet fried chicken and butter rice cakes.

586
00:25:14,361 --> 00:25:16,191
Eat sweet fried chicken at the beer festival.

587
00:25:16,461 --> 00:25:18,061
Butter rice cakes are free.

588
00:25:18,761 --> 00:25:21,371
The current score of the 13-dollar match.

589
00:25:22,001 --> 00:25:23,871
Extraordinary Couple and HunGry...

590
00:25:25,801 --> 00:25:27,200
have the same number of sales.

591
00:25:27,201 --> 00:25:28,441
(Surprised)

592
00:25:28,741 --> 00:25:30,210
- Oh, my gosh!
- Oh, my gosh!

593
00:25:30,211 --> 00:25:32,581
- Come and have sweet fried chicken!
- Come and have sweet fried chicken!

594
00:25:32,981 --> 00:25:34,141
Everyone!

595
00:25:34,751 --> 00:25:36,210
Oh, my gosh. Come to my booth.

596
00:25:36,211 --> 00:25:37,481
Come to my booth!

597
00:25:37,781 --> 00:25:39,221
- Truffle!
- I'll do it.

598
00:25:39,781 --> 00:25:41,490
(Extraordinary Couple and HunGry, 481 dollars, 37 units)

599
00:25:41,491 --> 00:25:44,521
Buy sweet fried chicken and get a butter rice cake for free.

600
00:25:44,861 --> 00:25:47,491
My food speaks for itself.

601
00:25:47,691 --> 00:25:49,731
Buy sweet fried chicken and get a butter rice cake for free.

602
00:25:51,461 --> 00:25:54,801
(The battle of the stars become more and more competitive.)

603
00:25:55,201 --> 00:25:57,571
I'm most curious about Seok Cheon and Ga Young.

604
00:25:58,501 --> 00:26:01,370
(Goal!, Don't Tell Grandma)

605
00:26:01,371 --> 00:26:02,371
(Hong Seok Cheon's Goal!)

606
00:26:02,372 --> 00:26:04,741
(Shin Ga Young's Don't Tell Grandma)

607
00:26:04,911 --> 00:26:06,240
Their dishes overlap in a way.

608
00:26:06,241 --> 00:26:08,110
- It's lasagna versus arancini.
- Really?

609
00:26:08,111 --> 00:26:09,980
(Roman crispy lasagna, crispy arancini and spicy seafood sauce)

610
00:26:09,981 --> 00:26:11,121
(8 dollars)

611
00:26:11,581 --> 00:26:13,351
They're both Italian food.

612
00:26:13,721 --> 00:26:16,550
I thought it was a popular Italian dish.

613
00:26:16,551 --> 00:26:19,520
(Deep-fried)

614
00:26:19,521 --> 00:26:20,521
(Which beer snack...)

615
00:26:20,522 --> 00:26:23,691
(will be chosen by the customers?)

616
00:26:26,331 --> 00:26:27,761
Ga Young, will you step out with a helmet on?

617
00:26:32,341 --> 00:26:33,371
How do I look?

618
00:26:33,941 --> 00:26:35,071
I can't see you face. It looks cute.

619
00:26:35,371 --> 00:26:36,571
You can see it's me, right?

620
00:26:36,811 --> 00:26:38,481
I can't really see your facial features.

621
00:26:39,411 --> 00:26:42,110
The opponent I chose just had to be the most famous person.

622
00:26:42,111 --> 00:26:46,221
We chose the most famous person on this show.

623
00:26:46,421 --> 00:26:48,751
(After Round 1 in Sejong ended)

624
00:26:49,191 --> 00:26:51,321
We chose Goal!

625
00:26:51,491 --> 00:26:53,560
He made his business big in Itaewon,

626
00:26:53,561 --> 00:26:55,390
and I want to beat him.

627
00:26:55,391 --> 00:26:57,160
- Us?
- Yes.

628
00:26:57,161 --> 00:26:58,630
(Don't Tell Grandma chose Goal!)

629
00:26:58,631 --> 00:27:00,900
(Sighing)

630
00:27:00,901 --> 00:27:05,171
We're not easy opponents, you know.

631
00:27:05,371 --> 00:27:08,440
For the last 20 years, not only have I run a restaurant...

632
00:27:08,441 --> 00:27:13,410
but a bar and a club as well. You must not know that.

633
00:27:13,411 --> 00:27:14,851
- He's an alcoholic.
- Yes.

634
00:27:15,181 --> 00:27:17,011
You better buckle up.

635
00:27:17,681 --> 00:27:21,491
For Round Two, you can reveal your face.

636
00:27:21,851 --> 00:27:23,520
Reveal your face.

637
00:27:23,521 --> 00:27:26,091
But you and your 1-on-1 opponent...

638
00:27:26,361 --> 00:27:28,861
must both agree to reveal the face.

639
00:27:29,431 --> 00:27:31,130
If you decide to keep it as a blind competition,

640
00:27:31,131 --> 00:27:33,461
you must wear a mask provided.

641
00:27:34,301 --> 00:27:36,171
- We better wear it.
- We should.

642
00:27:36,601 --> 00:27:39,441
If you think about it objectively, we have no choice.

643
00:27:39,801 --> 00:27:41,071
We can take it easy.

644
00:27:41,711 --> 00:27:43,211
We'll reveal our faces.

645
00:27:43,341 --> 00:27:44,411
We'll show our faces.

646
00:27:44,541 --> 00:27:45,680
- We'll show our faces.
- Our faces.

647
00:27:45,681 --> 00:27:46,880
(While everyone decided to reveal their faces)

648
00:27:46,881 --> 00:27:47,881
Our faces.

649
00:27:48,011 --> 00:27:50,011
If we go with the flow, we'll ruin our competition.

650
00:27:50,251 --> 00:27:51,851
We'll keep it as a blind competition.

651
00:27:52,551 --> 00:27:54,920
(They kept it as a blind competition.)

652
00:27:54,921 --> 00:27:56,951
With such young ones...

653
00:27:57,451 --> 00:28:01,391
Wear a mask or whatever. Do it your way.

654
00:28:01,931 --> 00:28:05,231
We're way behind experience when it comes to doing business.

655
00:28:05,461 --> 00:28:07,831
But we'll show them that they can lose badly...

656
00:28:07,931 --> 00:28:09,201
to their juniors.

657
00:28:09,431 --> 00:28:10,701
I'll win no matter what.

658
00:28:11,171 --> 00:28:13,900
We've drunk way more liquor than them,

659
00:28:13,901 --> 00:28:15,010
and we'd have thrown up...

660
00:28:15,011 --> 00:28:16,811
and passed out way more than they did as well.

661
00:28:17,311 --> 00:28:19,441
I don't think we'll lose.

662
00:28:19,911 --> 00:28:22,050
(The battle of pride between Class of 1989 and the 1989-born)

663
00:28:22,051 --> 00:28:23,811
(The battle of pride between the experienced and the rising star)

664
00:28:25,021 --> 00:28:26,151
Shall I go outside?

665
00:28:27,381 --> 00:28:29,221
Why can't you put it in?

666
00:28:29,591 --> 00:28:32,290
(Crowded)

667
00:28:32,291 --> 00:28:34,661
I'm sorry. You need to order.

668
00:28:35,461 --> 00:28:37,860
(He's wearing a mask too.)

669
00:28:37,861 --> 00:28:39,631
I wanted to start...

670
00:28:39,731 --> 00:28:42,430
receiving orders earlier than the opposing team.

671
00:28:42,431 --> 00:28:44,700
So I went all out as soon as we opened...

672
00:28:44,701 --> 00:28:46,301
to attract customers.

673
00:28:46,501 --> 00:28:49,711
And I wanted to make them stay in front of my booth.

674
00:28:50,611 --> 00:28:53,241
It's a game to throw a coin into a fish tank.

675
00:28:53,741 --> 00:28:55,210
"Did it go in or not?"

676
00:28:55,211 --> 00:28:58,281
I could turn it into an event.

677
00:28:58,621 --> 00:29:00,880
I thought it was a very good way...

678
00:29:00,881 --> 00:29:03,151
to keep the customers longer in front of my booth.

679
00:29:03,291 --> 00:29:05,261
Come and play a game.

680
00:29:05,761 --> 00:29:06,790
Throw it into here.

681
00:29:06,791 --> 00:29:08,530
- Throw it?
- Then I'll give you a gift.

682
00:29:08,531 --> 00:29:09,631
Let's go.

683
00:29:10,631 --> 00:29:13,761
It went in.

684
00:29:14,231 --> 00:29:17,500
If your order a lasagna, I'll give you one more.

685
00:29:17,501 --> 00:29:18,540
Okay.

686
00:29:18,541 --> 00:29:20,770
(Whir)

687
00:29:20,771 --> 00:29:21,811
Okay.

688
00:29:22,241 --> 00:29:24,011
- Let's start.
- Okay.

689
00:29:27,041 --> 00:29:28,681
We had a clear strategy.

690
00:29:29,281 --> 00:29:31,421
I'll do all the cooking.

691
00:29:31,721 --> 00:29:34,950
For attracting customers,

692
00:29:34,951 --> 00:29:37,950
Seok Cheon knows how to put on a perfect performance.

693
00:29:37,951 --> 00:29:39,361
Let's each do what we're best at.

694
00:29:40,821 --> 00:29:43,030
(Goal! has orders coming in nonstop.)

695
00:29:43,031 --> 00:29:44,091
Oh, my gosh.

696
00:29:47,761 --> 00:29:50,131
Put thick ragu sauce on the plate.

697
00:29:50,571 --> 00:29:53,401
Crispy lasagna, perilla leaf pesto,

698
00:29:54,141 --> 00:29:56,811
and sprinkle extra virgin olive oil mixed with herb oil.

699
00:29:57,441 --> 00:29:59,440
- How many are ready?
- Four.

700
00:29:59,441 --> 00:30:01,281
Please wait for a while. The food will be ready soon.

701
00:30:01,811 --> 00:30:03,050
Here you go.

702
00:30:03,051 --> 00:30:04,820
(Lasagna is served almost right after they order.)

703
00:30:04,821 --> 00:30:08,091
(The person in charge of cooking quickly prepares the food.)

704
00:30:08,151 --> 00:30:10,290
(The person in charge of sales promotes it.)

705
00:30:10,291 --> 00:30:11,560
- This is lasagna?
- You can't get this...

706
00:30:11,561 --> 00:30:12,820
at eight dollars elsewhere.

707
00:30:12,821 --> 00:30:16,291
- This is lasagna?
- Yes. We deep-fried the noodles.

708
00:30:16,531 --> 00:30:18,100
It's only eight dollars.

709
00:30:18,101 --> 00:30:19,530
You can order other food...

710
00:30:19,531 --> 00:30:21,671
and get this as an appetizer.

711
00:30:22,371 --> 00:30:23,931
- Do you want to try?
- Sure, let's.

712
00:30:26,971 --> 00:30:29,371
You're so shameless.

713
00:30:29,541 --> 00:30:30,741
You should throw it like this.

714
00:30:31,781 --> 00:30:32,781
That's right.

715
00:30:33,241 --> 00:30:35,251
Come and have arancini.

716
00:30:35,311 --> 00:30:36,651
(Empty)

717
00:30:38,781 --> 00:30:40,081
We're doomed.

718
00:30:42,091 --> 00:30:43,451
We're doomed.

719
00:30:45,191 --> 00:30:48,960
Seok Cheon is playing games with customers.

720
00:30:48,961 --> 00:30:49,961
Really?

721
00:30:50,291 --> 00:30:51,331
I'll go check it out.

722
00:30:52,631 --> 00:30:54,830
(Player exchanged)

723
00:30:54,831 --> 00:30:55,831
Hello.

724
00:30:56,171 --> 00:30:57,701
Come and have arancini.

725
00:30:57,801 --> 00:30:58,871
It's very delicious.

726
00:31:00,141 --> 00:31:02,070
Delicious Italian arancini.

727
00:31:02,071 --> 00:31:04,310
We have it with warm tomato sauce.

728
00:31:04,311 --> 00:31:06,911
We make it better than an Italian grandma.

729
00:31:07,381 --> 00:31:09,110
Hello. Come have arancini.

730
00:31:09,111 --> 00:31:10,780
You should definitely try.

731
00:31:10,781 --> 00:31:12,380
It's a bit spicy.

732
00:31:12,381 --> 00:31:15,191
We cooked it with tomato and seafood.

733
00:31:16,091 --> 00:31:18,051
We might lose at this rate.

734
00:31:18,421 --> 00:31:19,520
(Whir)

735
00:31:19,521 --> 00:31:20,561
We got an order.

736
00:31:20,621 --> 00:31:23,061
(Don't Tell Grandma's first order)

737
00:31:24,091 --> 00:31:25,100
(Current sales)

738
00:31:25,101 --> 00:31:27,001
We finally got an order.

739
00:31:27,261 --> 00:31:29,870
We didn't simply boil tomatoes for the tomato sauce.

740
00:31:29,871 --> 00:31:32,671
We stir-fried sea mussels and Manila clams in olive oil.

741
00:31:33,041 --> 00:31:35,441
In other words, we made shellfish broth.

742
00:31:36,171 --> 00:31:39,510
We use all the ingredients from their most basic forms...

743
00:31:39,511 --> 00:31:41,380
and cook from scratch, starting with the broth.

744
00:31:41,381 --> 00:31:43,611
I think we can definitely win with our food.

745
00:31:45,821 --> 00:31:48,551
Once the customers try our food and are satisfied with it,

746
00:31:48,851 --> 00:31:51,590
it could lead to other customers ordering from us.

747
00:31:51,591 --> 00:31:54,321
I hoped for that.

748
00:31:55,961 --> 00:31:58,461
- Please press that.
- Okay.

749
00:32:05,041 --> 00:32:06,641
- Try it.
- Are these meatballs?

750
00:32:06,841 --> 00:32:08,270
It's like a croquette. Try it.

751
00:32:08,271 --> 00:32:09,311
Here.

752
00:32:10,041 --> 00:32:12,111
Arancini is super tasty.

753
00:32:12,341 --> 00:32:13,441
It has rice inside.

754
00:32:14,481 --> 00:32:15,551
It's delicious.

755
00:32:15,711 --> 00:32:18,180
(Current sales: 168 dollars)

756
00:32:18,181 --> 00:32:20,020
We came back to order it again because it's so good.

757
00:32:20,021 --> 00:32:21,081
Thank you.

758
00:32:21,151 --> 00:32:22,190
It's really good.

759
00:32:22,191 --> 00:32:24,220
Really? We'll get it ready right away.

760
00:32:24,221 --> 00:32:25,260
Next...

761
00:32:25,261 --> 00:32:26,261
(Walking past)

762
00:32:26,262 --> 00:32:27,460
(Halts)

763
00:32:27,461 --> 00:32:29,331
Sagna, sagna, lasagna.

764
00:32:29,931 --> 00:32:31,360
Who wants some arancini?

765
00:32:31,361 --> 00:32:33,160
(The customers head to the lasagna booth.)

766
00:32:33,161 --> 00:32:34,331
Which sauce should we choose?

767
00:32:34,801 --> 00:32:36,470
Which sauce is good?

768
00:32:36,471 --> 00:32:38,071
Out of the five sauces,

769
00:32:38,941 --> 00:32:40,601
I'll give you every sauce you pick.

770
00:32:41,071 --> 00:32:44,371
The kick to our food today is the sauce, actually.

771
00:32:45,211 --> 00:32:46,310
Which sauce would you like?

772
00:32:46,311 --> 00:32:50,050
Seok Cheon said, "I want the customers..."

773
00:32:50,051 --> 00:32:52,681
"to feel like they're customizing their own dish."

774
00:32:52,921 --> 00:32:54,991
Would you like 3? You're only supposed to get 1,

775
00:32:55,251 --> 00:32:56,451
but since we just opened...

776
00:32:56,921 --> 00:33:01,590
We made five different sauces.

777
00:33:01,591 --> 00:33:03,260
They all taste different,

778
00:33:03,261 --> 00:33:05,231
and the customers can choose different flavours.

779
00:33:05,701 --> 00:33:07,700
Milk cream made of vanilla beans.

780
00:33:07,701 --> 00:33:08,970
- Buldak sauce.
- Buldak sauce.

781
00:33:08,971 --> 00:33:11,430
I gave him the mayonnaise and herb sauce too.

782
00:33:11,431 --> 00:33:14,241
Herb oil and garlic saffron sauce.

783
00:33:14,971 --> 00:33:18,241
(5 sauces which actively utilize commercial products)

784
00:33:18,411 --> 00:33:20,110
It's shown like this.

785
00:33:20,111 --> 00:33:21,411
(They can check the opponents' ingredients.)

786
00:33:22,881 --> 00:33:25,181
Buldak sauce? My gosh.

787
00:33:25,951 --> 00:33:28,121
What is banana-flavoured milk for?

788
00:33:28,691 --> 00:33:30,451
How is he going to use that?

789
00:33:31,021 --> 00:33:33,860
Many of the ingredients were...

790
00:33:33,861 --> 00:33:36,831
the sauces sold on the market.

791
00:33:37,461 --> 00:33:39,200
Making good use of commercial products...

792
00:33:39,201 --> 00:33:41,101
is a good skill when you do business.

793
00:33:41,161 --> 00:33:44,030
Did I make an absurd choice...

794
00:33:44,031 --> 00:33:45,901
by making the broth from scratch?

795
00:33:46,371 --> 00:33:47,840
You can have whatever you like.

796
00:33:47,841 --> 00:33:50,771
The sauces are amazing today.

797
00:33:51,681 --> 00:33:53,141
- I'm curious.
- Right?

798
00:33:54,281 --> 00:33:55,411
He's a sauce maniac.

799
00:33:56,151 --> 00:33:57,281
The chef.

800
00:33:57,951 --> 00:33:59,181
This is lasagna.

801
00:33:59,481 --> 00:34:00,481
- Lasagna?
- Lasagna.

802
00:34:01,521 --> 00:34:03,091
The sauce tastes good.

803
00:34:04,121 --> 00:34:05,761
It tastes good because there are many sauces.

804
00:34:06,761 --> 00:34:08,190
- Because we added this.
- Yes.

805
00:34:08,191 --> 00:34:09,891
It became tastier by adding one more sauce.

806
00:34:10,091 --> 00:34:11,161
That was a smart move.

807
00:34:11,491 --> 00:34:13,431
The sauce is really delicious.

808
00:34:13,661 --> 00:34:16,201
It's not too salty, and it's strong enough.

809
00:34:16,271 --> 00:34:18,970
We make many tasty dishes,

810
00:34:18,971 --> 00:34:20,470
and we were proud of ourselves.

811
00:34:20,471 --> 00:34:23,570
But he really gave off the vibe of a veteran.

812
00:34:23,571 --> 00:34:26,341
- Saffron.
- Saffron. The expensive sauce.

813
00:34:26,411 --> 00:34:29,910
(1st half, Hong Seok Cheon's sales versus Shin Ga Young's sales)

814
00:34:29,911 --> 00:34:32,750
(Hong Seok Cheon: 464 dollars. Shin Ga Young: 384 dollars.)

815
00:34:32,751 --> 00:34:36,521
(1st half, Hong Seok Cheon wins, Shin Ga Young loses.)

816
00:34:41,091 --> 00:34:43,230
Will you keep it as a blind competition?

817
00:34:43,231 --> 00:34:44,461
(Edward Kwon versus Lim Ki Hak)

818
00:34:44,861 --> 00:34:47,330
No. We'll compete with our faces revealed.

819
00:34:47,331 --> 00:34:48,570
(To be continued in 60 seconds)

820
00:34:48,571 --> 00:34:51,771
(Ma Restaurant versus Bol A Bol)

821
00:34:52,201 --> 00:34:55,571
(In front of Lim Ki Hak's Bol A Bol)

822
00:34:59,310 --> 00:35:02,450
(In front of Lim Ki Hak's Bol A Bol)

823
00:35:03,820 --> 00:35:05,719
(The customer passes his booth and heads to the next one.)

824
00:35:05,720 --> 00:35:07,919
- Hello.
- Hello.

825
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:09,220
Hello.

826
00:35:09,360 --> 00:35:10,390
Beijing duck?

827
00:35:11,090 --> 00:35:12,660
I really like Beijing duck.

828
00:35:13,560 --> 00:35:14,990
That's a big portion.

829
00:35:16,530 --> 00:35:17,860
They serve mianbao xia too?

830
00:35:19,230 --> 00:35:20,570
- One more.
- It looks so good.

831
00:35:21,230 --> 00:35:23,840
(Edward Kwon's Ma Restaurant)

832
00:35:24,370 --> 00:35:28,710
(He is busily preparing Ma Restaurant's menus.)

833
00:35:29,310 --> 00:35:31,339
The French dishes you can cook...

834
00:35:31,340 --> 00:35:33,380
as beer snacks...

835
00:35:33,450 --> 00:35:34,550
are more or less...

836
00:35:35,180 --> 00:35:37,050
predictable.

837
00:35:37,450 --> 00:35:40,389
- It's 25 dollars.
- It's a bit pricy.

838
00:35:40,390 --> 00:35:43,420
We'd need to make a platter in this case.

839
00:35:44,520 --> 00:35:46,129
The best option for them...

840
00:35:46,130 --> 00:35:47,390
is a platter.

841
00:35:47,860 --> 00:35:50,060
A platter. To sell a menu that's worth 25 dollars,

842
00:35:50,560 --> 00:35:52,469
their only option is to sell a big platter...

843
00:35:52,470 --> 00:35:53,670
with many different foods.

844
00:35:54,430 --> 00:35:56,669
We'll only find out for sure when we start the competition,

845
00:35:56,670 --> 00:35:58,469
but I thought people would...

846
00:35:58,470 --> 00:36:01,879
either like or dislike a classical French dish, no in between.

847
00:36:01,880 --> 00:36:04,739
So I thought,

848
00:36:04,740 --> 00:36:06,579
"An unfamiliar menu..."

849
00:36:06,580 --> 00:36:09,179
"might not get chosen."

850
00:36:09,180 --> 00:36:11,650
"Why would I bother to take the risk?"

851
00:36:12,190 --> 00:36:15,320
What Chinese dishes can we sell?

852
00:36:16,760 --> 00:36:18,630
It has to serve both as a meal and a beer snack.

853
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:20,559
Based on the time,

854
00:36:20,560 --> 00:36:23,229
you'll get orders from people who want a full meal.

855
00:36:23,230 --> 00:36:25,670
So the dish needs to make them full,

856
00:36:25,970 --> 00:36:27,429
and at the same time, it should be something...

857
00:36:27,430 --> 00:36:28,870
they rarely find in beer festivals.

858
00:36:29,270 --> 00:36:30,940
So I prepared Beijing duck.

859
00:36:36,180 --> 00:36:37,210
Shrimp mianbao xia.

860
00:36:38,010 --> 00:36:39,779
And there's a Taiwanese sandwich...

861
00:36:39,780 --> 00:36:41,109
called cong you bing.

862
00:36:41,110 --> 00:36:42,750
(Cong you bing, a traditional snack enjoyed in Taiwan and Shandong)

863
00:36:43,650 --> 00:36:47,090
(Beijing duck, mala cong you bing, and mianbao xia, 25 dollars)

864
00:36:47,520 --> 00:36:48,559
(This menu surprised everyone as much as charcuterie platter.)

865
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:49,720
- Charcuterie platter.
- What?

866
00:36:50,760 --> 00:36:52,459
- Beijing duck.
- Beijing duck?

867
00:36:52,460 --> 00:36:53,529
(Beijing duck, mala cong you bing, and mianbao xia)

868
00:36:53,530 --> 00:36:54,830
He's selling Beijing duck?

869
00:36:54,990 --> 00:36:57,800
- Beijing duck? How's that possible?
- Beijing duck.

870
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:01,699
Mianbao xia, Beijing duck, and mala cong you bing...

871
00:37:01,700 --> 00:37:02,770
for 25 dollars?

872
00:37:03,140 --> 00:37:04,240
How will he cook Beijing duck?

873
00:37:07,040 --> 00:37:09,240
- I didn't see this coming.
- I didn't imagine this.

874
00:37:09,740 --> 00:37:11,610
Their menu is very filling.

875
00:37:11,950 --> 00:37:14,879
"I've wanted to try this dish before,"

876
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:16,249
"and I can try it here."

877
00:37:16,250 --> 00:37:18,049
"What's more, at this price."

878
00:37:18,050 --> 00:37:21,020
For Beijing duck, if you go to a hotel,

879
00:37:21,320 --> 00:37:22,720
you need to make a reservation in advance.

880
00:37:22,890 --> 00:37:24,860
If you follow the protocol, it will take some time.

881
00:37:25,360 --> 00:37:27,660
(Air inserted to separate the meat from the skin)

882
00:37:28,060 --> 00:37:30,230
The ducks need to be dry-aged...

883
00:37:30,660 --> 00:37:33,299
and roasted while oil is poured...

884
00:37:33,300 --> 00:37:34,429
onto them continuously.

885
00:37:34,430 --> 00:37:35,800
(Beijing duck needs to be roasted for at least 1 hour.)

886
00:37:35,940 --> 00:37:38,839
It's slightly different, but we'll use a method...

887
00:37:38,840 --> 00:37:41,910
to make smoked ducks almost as crispy as the real deal.

888
00:37:42,210 --> 00:37:45,139
We'll grill them for 20 minutes at 180℃.

889
00:37:45,140 --> 00:37:46,179
(A simplified Beijing duck recipe using an oven)

890
00:37:46,180 --> 00:37:48,950
But let's place the oven outside.

891
00:37:49,680 --> 00:37:52,720
The most important aspect of a non-blind competition is...

892
00:37:53,320 --> 00:37:55,990
that you must grab their attention with every aspect you have.

893
00:37:56,160 --> 00:37:57,819
And what's the first step?

894
00:37:57,820 --> 00:37:59,230
Let the smell spread.

895
00:38:00,060 --> 00:38:02,529
And they need to be able to see...

896
00:38:02,530 --> 00:38:05,230
the meat being grilled and so on.

897
00:38:07,070 --> 00:38:09,940
(The Beijing duck is taken out of the oven when the order comes in.)

898
00:38:10,840 --> 00:38:13,670
(It is prepared right in front of their eyes.)

899
00:38:15,840 --> 00:38:18,440
For cong you bing, grill both sides on a pan.

900
00:38:19,150 --> 00:38:21,750
Apply mala sauce on it.

901
00:38:22,320 --> 00:38:24,819
Put stir-fried vegetables,

902
00:38:24,820 --> 00:38:26,749
roll it like gimbap, and serve it.

903
00:38:26,750 --> 00:38:29,389
Shall we make one nice sample?

904
00:38:29,390 --> 00:38:30,689
Okay, got it.

905
00:38:30,690 --> 00:38:32,890
(Setting up a sampler dish)

906
00:38:33,490 --> 00:38:36,530
(Ma Restaurant's Peking duck meal)

907
00:38:37,030 --> 00:38:41,630
(Edward Kwon's Peking duck versus Lim Ki Hak's charcuterie platter)

908
00:38:41,670 --> 00:38:44,700
(Ma Restaurant)

909
00:38:45,370 --> 00:38:48,010
You know duck, right? It's delicious.

910
00:38:48,470 --> 00:38:51,479
Peking duck, mianbao xia, and cong you bing.

911
00:38:51,480 --> 00:38:52,549
Is this a meal?

912
00:38:52,550 --> 00:38:54,249
Yes, it's a meal.

913
00:38:54,250 --> 00:38:57,380
You wrap it up, dip it in the sweet bean sauce,

914
00:38:57,480 --> 00:38:58,550
and enjoy it.

915
00:39:00,220 --> 00:39:02,490
(Payment complete)

916
00:39:02,890 --> 00:39:04,019
One meal.

917
00:39:04,020 --> 00:39:05,860
- Okay, one meal.
- Good.

918
00:39:06,030 --> 00:39:07,390
- Nice.
- Hi.

919
00:39:09,430 --> 00:39:10,830
It's Peking duck.

920
00:39:12,030 --> 00:39:13,170
It looks good.

921
00:39:13,970 --> 00:39:15,800
- This is how it's served.
- Cool.

922
00:39:16,140 --> 00:39:17,369
- Hi.
- What a big serving.

923
00:39:17,370 --> 00:39:18,910
- Hi.
- Hi.

924
00:39:19,970 --> 00:39:20,970
Awesome.

925
00:39:22,410 --> 00:39:24,880
(Thanks to the sampler, orders keep coming in.)

926
00:39:25,480 --> 00:39:27,250
Just keep frying it.

927
00:39:37,890 --> 00:39:39,759
- Here are the chopsticks.
- What's this sauce?

928
00:39:39,760 --> 00:39:42,100
This is Sriracha mayo.

929
00:39:42,300 --> 00:39:43,729
It's a dip for the fried items.

930
00:39:43,730 --> 00:39:45,199
Do you mind telling me how to eat it?

931
00:39:45,200 --> 00:39:47,470
- All right. Add some of the sauce.
- Okay.

932
00:39:47,500 --> 00:39:48,500
Add in the other sauce,

933
00:39:48,501 --> 00:39:50,399
seasoned green onions, cucumbers, duck,

934
00:39:50,400 --> 00:39:52,539
and deep-fried ramyeon. Wrap it up.

935
00:39:52,540 --> 00:39:53,840
I see.

936
00:39:54,210 --> 00:39:56,979
- Peking duck.
- Thank you. It's my first time.

937
00:39:56,980 --> 00:39:58,340
- Is it?
- Yes.

938
00:39:58,610 --> 00:39:59,980
That should be your number.

939
00:40:00,180 --> 00:40:02,120
(Payment complete)

940
00:40:02,450 --> 00:40:03,549
Another order.

941
00:40:03,550 --> 00:40:04,850
- Got it.
- Two more orders.

942
00:40:05,450 --> 00:40:07,350
- Two more coming up.
- Two more.

943
00:40:09,760 --> 00:40:11,919
- You ordered 2, right?
- Yes, I ordered 2.

944
00:40:11,920 --> 00:40:14,359
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

945
00:40:14,360 --> 00:40:16,299
- Enjoy.
- Yes, sir.

946
00:40:16,300 --> 00:40:17,930
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

947
00:40:23,500 --> 00:40:26,010
Chef Edward Kwon's booth...

948
00:40:27,010 --> 00:40:28,310
had many orders.

949
00:40:29,540 --> 00:40:30,640
He was busy.

950
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:32,050
But we...

951
00:40:35,280 --> 00:40:36,880
Things are different compared to Round One.

952
00:40:37,150 --> 00:40:38,150
You're right.

953
00:40:39,690 --> 00:40:42,119
(Stepping out for a bit)

954
00:40:42,120 --> 00:40:43,359
The deep-fried shrimps are good.

955
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:46,030
What's more, the first 60 customers get deep-fried ginseng on the house.

956
00:40:47,630 --> 00:40:49,160
Amazing. Gotgan...

957
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:50,959
is plating outside,

958
00:40:50,960 --> 00:40:52,730
- so there's a line of people.
- Really?

959
00:40:53,470 --> 00:40:55,700
(Right now, the Street Beer Festival is...)

960
00:40:56,840 --> 00:40:59,940
Miss, don't forget to take one ginseng.

961
00:40:59,970 --> 00:41:02,909
Grated truffle, exclusive today only!

962
00:41:02,910 --> 00:41:04,809
- Come try it.
- You didn't bring money?

963
00:41:04,810 --> 00:41:06,710
- Pay after you try it.
- Did you bring money?

964
00:41:06,950 --> 00:41:08,449
If it's bad, you don't have to buy it.

965
00:41:08,450 --> 00:41:09,549
(A generous sample-tasting event)

966
00:41:09,550 --> 00:41:10,620
Try it. Hi.

967
00:41:11,120 --> 00:41:13,350
(A performance that grabs both the eye and the ear)

968
00:41:15,020 --> 00:41:17,719
Those ideas didn't even cross my mind.

969
00:41:17,720 --> 00:41:21,690
Are famous chefs different for a reason?

970
00:41:22,530 --> 00:41:23,830
It's all about touting.

971
00:41:24,600 --> 00:41:27,930
I'm a very introverted person.

972
00:41:31,170 --> 00:41:33,169
- Hi.
- Hi.

973
00:41:33,170 --> 00:41:34,269
I greeted the customers...

974
00:41:34,270 --> 00:41:36,040
- passing by...
- Hi.

975
00:41:36,340 --> 00:41:37,410
- and such.
- Hi.

976
00:41:40,450 --> 00:41:43,249
(As soon as customers approach)

977
00:41:43,250 --> 00:41:45,620
I'm getting all shy and can't stay outside.

978
00:41:47,590 --> 00:41:49,390
I can't blame it solely on my personality,

979
00:41:49,920 --> 00:41:52,890
but I didn't know how to draw in customers.

980
00:41:53,290 --> 00:41:54,590
Why not show customers...

981
00:41:54,760 --> 00:41:56,799
your face while pouring the ice?

982
00:41:56,800 --> 00:41:58,129
I doubt anyone knows me.

983
00:41:58,130 --> 00:41:59,870
I'm sure they do.

984
00:42:00,370 --> 00:42:03,400
(Courageously stepping outside again)

985
00:42:04,500 --> 00:42:07,070
(Ma Restaurant, Bol A Bol)

986
00:42:07,440 --> 00:42:09,440
- Hi.
- Hi.

987
00:42:09,910 --> 00:42:12,010
- I've been to L'espoir.
- Thank you.

988
00:42:12,850 --> 00:42:14,910
(The first customer recognised Chef Lim Ki Hak.)

989
00:42:15,280 --> 00:42:16,280
Thank you.

990
00:42:20,020 --> 00:42:21,690
- We're getting an order.
- Got it.

991
00:42:23,290 --> 00:42:24,790
(Rushing)

992
00:42:25,630 --> 00:42:27,160
I'm happy to get an order.

993
00:42:27,330 --> 00:42:28,360
Same here.

994
00:42:28,660 --> 00:42:31,360
(Bol A Bol gets its 1st order after 22 minutes.)

995
00:42:31,860 --> 00:42:35,230
(Preparing the dish with care)

996
00:42:35,940 --> 00:42:37,070
Is it all golden?

997
00:42:37,370 --> 00:42:38,370
Yes.

998
00:42:38,371 --> 00:42:40,869
We made sure the dish was easy to make...

999
00:42:40,870 --> 00:42:42,809
- and serve.
- True.

1000
00:42:42,810 --> 00:42:43,839
(The order is served in no time.)

1001
00:42:43,840 --> 00:42:44,840
Give me a second.

1002
00:42:45,950 --> 00:42:47,510
Hi. Enjoy.

1003
00:42:48,480 --> 00:42:51,050
It's mashed potatoes under the Lyon-style sausage.

1004
00:42:51,280 --> 00:42:53,250
This right here is carrot rapee with walnuts in it.

1005
00:42:53,390 --> 00:42:55,619
There's also pate en croute and roulade.

1006
00:42:55,620 --> 00:42:57,060
Dijon mustard, cornichon,

1007
00:42:57,220 --> 00:42:58,759
and parmesan cheese...

1008
00:42:58,760 --> 00:42:59,930
- are beer snacks.
- Thank you.

1009
00:43:00,090 --> 00:43:01,430
If only there were wine. It's a bummer...

1010
00:43:01,530 --> 00:43:02,660
- this is a beer festival.
- Right.

1011
00:43:03,130 --> 00:43:04,329
It's good with beer too,

1012
00:43:04,330 --> 00:43:05,429
so give it a shot.

1013
00:43:05,430 --> 00:43:06,530
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

1014
00:43:08,130 --> 00:43:09,869
Pate wrapped in bread.

1015
00:43:09,870 --> 00:43:11,469
(The first taste of Bol A Bol)

1016
00:43:11,470 --> 00:43:12,540
Let's try one each.

1017
00:43:25,890 --> 00:43:27,050
- It's good.
- Delicious, isn't it?

1018
00:43:28,590 --> 00:43:29,790
- The fat.
- Yes?

1019
00:43:30,220 --> 00:43:32,230
The crunchy texture of the fat is nice.

1020
00:43:32,430 --> 00:43:33,960
I can't figure out which part is the fat.

1021
00:43:36,160 --> 00:43:38,030
The pate itself is good. It's good pate.

1022
00:43:39,270 --> 00:43:40,630
The dish is new to me.

1023
00:43:40,700 --> 00:43:42,370
Pate is an unfamiliar taste, right?

1024
00:43:46,570 --> 00:43:47,940
Are we the first and last customers?

1025
00:43:49,110 --> 00:43:50,110
But it's good.

1026
00:43:51,040 --> 00:43:53,610
I guess 25 dollars is a little pricey.

1027
00:43:55,880 --> 00:43:58,419
The restaurant next to us is selling quite well.

1028
00:43:58,420 --> 00:43:59,450
Is that so?

1029
00:44:00,250 --> 00:44:02,290
(Current Revenue of Bol A Bol: 25 dollars)

1030
00:44:02,620 --> 00:44:04,490
We need to keep going.

1031
00:44:04,590 --> 00:44:05,590
Understood.

1032
00:44:05,860 --> 00:44:07,660
Seven orders must be served.

1033
00:44:07,960 --> 00:44:09,529
- You know how to eat it, right?
- Yes.

1034
00:44:09,530 --> 00:44:11,199
Wrap it up well and enjoy it.

1035
00:44:11,200 --> 00:44:13,930
If you wrap it with the sauce inside...

1036
00:44:14,370 --> 00:44:16,070
- Oh, my.
- Thank you.

1037
00:44:16,300 --> 00:44:17,899
- Enjoy the dish.
- Thank you,.

1038
00:44:17,900 --> 00:44:19,069
Here are the chopsticks...

1039
00:44:19,070 --> 00:44:20,870
- and spoons for the sauce.
- Got it.

1040
00:44:21,070 --> 00:44:22,639
- Do you know how to eat it?
- Yes.

1041
00:44:22,640 --> 00:44:24,880
It's bound to be good if you wrap one well.

1042
00:44:26,180 --> 00:44:29,180
(Customers who ordered Edward Kwon's Peking duck)

1043
00:44:32,320 --> 00:44:33,920
- Doesn't it have a clean taste?
- It does.

1044
00:44:34,790 --> 00:44:36,459
It's my first time having Peking duck,

1045
00:44:36,460 --> 00:44:37,490
and it's not greasy at all.

1046
00:44:38,320 --> 00:44:41,330
(Shrimp mianbao xia)

1047
00:44:44,960 --> 00:44:47,600
This for 25 dollars...

1048
00:44:48,300 --> 00:44:50,700
I would even buy it for 35 dollars.

1049
00:44:52,310 --> 00:44:54,139
(Peking duck, shrimp mianbao xia)

1050
00:44:54,140 --> 00:44:56,080
It's a menu you can only get at high-end restaurants.

1051
00:44:56,610 --> 00:44:59,450
Being able to eat all this at this price...

1052
00:45:00,050 --> 00:45:01,850
is a real bargain. What a deal.

1053
00:45:08,690 --> 00:45:09,920
I won't have enough vegetables.

1054
00:45:10,960 --> 00:45:11,990
Let's ask.

1055
00:45:14,960 --> 00:45:16,030
Of course.

1056
00:45:17,400 --> 00:45:19,030
- Here, vegetables.
- Vegetables?

1057
00:45:20,430 --> 00:45:21,829
- Here. Enjoy.
- Thank you.

1058
00:45:21,830 --> 00:45:22,840
Thank you.

1059
00:45:23,540 --> 00:45:25,139
May we get a bit more vegetables?

1060
00:45:25,140 --> 00:45:26,970
Vegetables? Sure, coming right up.

1061
00:45:27,210 --> 00:45:28,709
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

1062
00:45:28,710 --> 00:45:30,480
- Have a pleasant meal.
- Thank you.

1063
00:45:31,240 --> 00:45:33,550
After seeing customers ask...

1064
00:45:33,610 --> 00:45:37,180
for more seasoned green onions one after another,

1065
00:45:37,280 --> 00:45:40,950
I felt we could get a high satisfaction rate.

1066
00:45:41,650 --> 00:45:42,719
(Sighing)

1067
00:45:42,720 --> 00:45:43,760
Are you busy?

1068
00:45:43,860 --> 00:45:45,760
Why did I choose such a complicated dish?

1069
00:45:47,460 --> 00:45:48,560
I was jealous.

1070
00:45:50,530 --> 00:45:52,160
I've always wanted to try pate.

1071
00:45:58,500 --> 00:46:00,569
That's weird. Why are so many customers leaving...

1072
00:46:00,570 --> 00:46:03,510
after just tapping on the kiosk?

1073
00:46:03,880 --> 00:46:05,680
It's hard to get customers to pay.

1074
00:46:06,310 --> 00:46:09,150
They tap on the kiosk with their credit cards in hand.

1075
00:46:10,950 --> 00:46:11,950
(Tilting)

1076
00:46:14,250 --> 00:46:15,589
He just left.

1077
00:46:15,590 --> 00:46:18,060
Because it's a dish they've never tried before...

1078
00:46:18,620 --> 00:46:20,730
The customers seem unfamiliar with it.

1079
00:46:21,290 --> 00:46:23,160
I can't even grasp what kind of dish it is.

1080
00:46:23,960 --> 00:46:26,470
- I know, right?
- Something like ham or bread?

1081
00:46:27,870 --> 00:46:30,500
- The bread...
- There's sausage inside the bread.

1082
00:46:32,000 --> 00:46:36,040
Even the word "charcuterie" itself seemed to be new to the customers.

1083
00:46:36,980 --> 00:46:38,340
It's like a breakfast menu.

1084
00:46:38,840 --> 00:46:43,280
I thought it was still a very unfamiliar dish.

1085
00:46:43,820 --> 00:46:45,790
When coming up with the menu,

1086
00:46:46,150 --> 00:46:49,390
I also thought of French cuisine.

1087
00:46:50,190 --> 00:46:51,889
But considering various aspects,

1088
00:46:51,890 --> 00:46:53,560
including the nature of the beer festival,

1089
00:46:53,730 --> 00:46:55,860
I worried that no customers would buy the dish.

1090
00:46:57,760 --> 00:47:01,700
I wanted to win with the dish,

1091
00:47:01,900 --> 00:47:04,970
but no customers were buying our food.

1092
00:47:05,970 --> 00:47:09,070
(Bol A Bol didn't even get a chance to show off the dish.)

1093
00:47:10,610 --> 00:47:12,039
It's impossible to predict what's coming next.

1094
00:47:12,040 --> 00:47:13,510
(Bol A Bol's 1st half orders: 7)

1095
00:47:13,950 --> 00:47:15,479
(Edward Kwon: 945 dollars, Lim Ki Hak: 182 dollars)

1096
00:47:15,480 --> 00:47:18,479
(Edward Kwon: Won, Lim Ki Hak: Lost)

1097
00:47:18,480 --> 00:47:20,420
Thank you. Have a pleasant meal.

1098
00:47:22,120 --> 00:47:25,059
(Current time: 6pm)

1099
00:47:25,060 --> 00:47:27,890
(Surpassed 1,000 attendees)

1100
00:47:28,190 --> 00:47:29,359
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

1101
00:47:29,360 --> 00:47:31,160
- Are you okay in that seat?
- Yes.

1102
00:47:32,670 --> 00:47:34,000
Which booth has the most customers?

1103
00:47:34,400 --> 00:47:36,740
There's a huge line at Chef Kim Hee Eun's booth.

1104
00:47:36,800 --> 00:47:38,570
- The ingredient cost...
- Many are at Chef Kim Hee Eun's.

1105
00:47:39,770 --> 00:47:41,569
It's coming right up.

1106
00:47:41,570 --> 00:47:43,480
(A crowd in the 13-dollar price range)

1107
00:47:43,610 --> 00:47:45,810
(HunGry's cream shrimp and sweet fried chicken)

1108
00:47:46,180 --> 00:47:47,749
- Me too.
- The sweet fried chicken is good.

1109
00:47:47,750 --> 00:47:49,049
Let me try the cream shrimp.

1110
00:47:49,050 --> 00:47:50,349
How's the sweet fried chicken?

1111
00:47:50,350 --> 00:47:51,820
Is it like your typical sweet fried chicken?

1112
00:47:53,020 --> 00:47:54,150
It's juicy.

1113
00:47:54,350 --> 00:47:55,520
- It's good.
- Right?

1114
00:47:55,890 --> 00:47:56,959
- The sauce is a surprise.
- It's not really your typical...

1115
00:47:56,960 --> 00:47:58,019
sweet fried chicken.

1116
00:47:58,020 --> 00:47:59,059
- Is that so?
- You can really taste...

1117
00:47:59,060 --> 00:48:00,060
the black pepper.

1118
00:48:01,360 --> 00:48:02,659
- It's good.
- It's not like store-bought food.

1119
00:48:02,660 --> 00:48:04,760
How does it compare to the sweet fried chicken in Sokcho?

1120
00:48:05,760 --> 00:48:06,930
- This is better.
- This is better.

1121
00:48:08,330 --> 00:48:10,499
It was 13 dollars or 15 dollars.

1122
00:48:10,500 --> 00:48:12,069
- This was 15 dollars.
- For real?

1123
00:48:12,070 --> 00:48:13,809
- Yes.
- It's 13 dollars.

1124
00:48:13,810 --> 00:48:15,469
- It's worth it.
- Yes, it's justifiable.

1125
00:48:15,470 --> 00:48:17,179
Everything is topped off with truffles.

1126
00:48:17,180 --> 00:48:19,410
There are truffles and button mushrooms.

1127
00:48:20,010 --> 00:48:21,280
This must be gnocchi.

1128
00:48:21,810 --> 00:48:23,450
- Yes, it's gnocchi.
- Because it's gnocchi?

1129
00:48:23,950 --> 00:48:25,480
Is it worth 13 dollars?

1130
00:48:25,820 --> 00:48:29,119
(Gnocchi)

1131
00:48:29,120 --> 00:48:30,359
- Pork belly?
- Is it good?

1132
00:48:30,360 --> 00:48:31,590
- It's good.
- Pork belly?

1133
00:48:31,720 --> 00:48:32,860
The sauce is good.

1134
00:48:34,630 --> 00:48:36,559
You can really smell the truffle.

1135
00:48:36,560 --> 00:48:38,460
There's actual grated truffle on top.

1136
00:48:38,500 --> 00:48:40,669
It's good. The dish is worth 13 dollars.

1137
00:48:40,670 --> 00:48:41,729
Right?

1138
00:48:41,730 --> 00:48:43,299
- We're done.
- Which did you like best?

1139
00:48:43,300 --> 00:48:45,270
- Yes.
- Me? The sweet fried chicken.

1140
00:48:45,540 --> 00:48:47,240
The cream shrimp among these dishes.

1141
00:48:47,340 --> 00:48:49,680
Honestly, based on the sauce alone, I choose this one.

1142
00:48:50,580 --> 00:48:51,739
- Me too.
- It's gone.

1143
00:48:51,740 --> 00:48:52,779
- Really?
- It was the sauce.

1144
00:48:52,780 --> 00:48:55,509
It's really good. I'm scraping the sauce off.

1145
00:48:55,510 --> 00:48:57,580
I agree. It's the sauce for me too.

1146
00:48:58,120 --> 00:49:00,889
Looking around, many people chose this dish.

1147
00:49:00,890 --> 00:49:03,489
Right? It goes well with beer. I like it.

1148
00:49:03,490 --> 00:49:05,190
- It...
- Almost everyone ordered it.

1149
00:49:05,720 --> 00:49:07,260
It's on every table.

1150
00:49:08,830 --> 00:49:13,970
(The most ordered dish right now is the sweet fried chicken.)

1151
00:49:14,070 --> 00:49:15,099
- Is anyone's order up?
- It's hot.

1152
00:49:15,100 --> 00:49:16,800
- Real truffle, not truffle oil.
- One sweet fried chicken.

1153
00:49:17,300 --> 00:49:18,740
Gosh, I'm struggling here.

1154
00:49:19,000 --> 00:49:21,270
In the 13-dollar price range,

1155
00:49:21,810 --> 00:49:24,980
HunGry has turned the tables on Extraordinary Couple.

1156
00:49:26,210 --> 00:49:28,580
I'm all over the place. This is bad.

1157
00:49:29,520 --> 00:49:31,050
Three sweet fried chickens, please.

1158
00:49:31,320 --> 00:49:34,450
(The warmer is being emptied in no time.)

1159
00:49:36,960 --> 00:49:38,020
We're sold out.

1160
00:49:38,320 --> 00:49:39,360
Nice.

1161
00:49:40,530 --> 00:49:42,999
- Here, thank you. Enjoy.
- Thank you.

1162
00:49:43,000 --> 00:49:44,100
Do you need a fork?

1163
00:49:47,300 --> 00:49:49,900
Oh, my gosh. Hold on. It has to be served in order.

1164
00:49:50,770 --> 00:49:51,799
Number 606.

1165
00:49:51,800 --> 00:49:53,210
No, number 606 should be here.

1166
00:49:53,440 --> 00:49:54,569
We can't mess it up.

1167
00:49:54,570 --> 00:49:55,810
Numbers 1654 and 954.

1168
00:49:56,140 --> 00:49:57,380
We're selling more than expected.

1169
00:49:58,340 --> 00:49:59,850
It's a good thing. 2594 and 4954.

1170
00:50:02,480 --> 00:50:03,720
The line is super long.

1171
00:50:04,120 --> 00:50:05,250
- The line?
- Yes.

1172
00:50:05,380 --> 00:50:07,990
We're almost done with the sweet fried chicken.

1173
00:50:08,690 --> 00:50:09,760
- For real?
- Yes.

1174
00:50:10,090 --> 00:50:11,560
This isn't good.

1175
00:50:13,390 --> 00:50:15,590
(The orders keep coming in.)

1176
00:50:17,260 --> 00:50:18,760
We got a total of 65 orders.

1177
00:50:19,800 --> 00:50:21,230
- We got 65?
- Yes.

1178
00:50:21,900 --> 00:50:24,100
Oh, dear. Shouldn't we stop taking orders?

1179
00:50:25,540 --> 00:50:26,769
(HunGry prepared 70 portions.)

1180
00:50:26,770 --> 00:50:28,409
Can't we sell 65? We prepared 70.

1181
00:50:28,410 --> 00:50:29,540
Because it's 65?

1182
00:50:30,210 --> 00:50:31,239
Oh, no.

1183
00:50:31,240 --> 00:50:33,350
(Limited ingredients remaining.)

1184
00:50:33,880 --> 00:50:35,980
Honey, are we low on anything?

1185
00:50:36,150 --> 00:50:37,150
No.

1186
00:50:38,320 --> 00:50:40,820
The orders are backing up. This won't do.

1187
00:50:42,320 --> 00:50:46,090
(Checking out the next-door restaurant's situation.)

1188
00:50:46,590 --> 00:50:47,889
Truffle. Real truffle.

1189
00:50:47,890 --> 00:50:50,629
(Selling without a break.)

1190
00:50:50,630 --> 00:50:52,499
We prepared 70 portions.

1191
00:50:52,500 --> 00:50:54,199
Without any ingredients, we couldn't sell anything.

1192
00:50:54,200 --> 00:50:57,040
Everything we prepared has sold out.

1193
00:50:58,240 --> 00:51:00,870
(Rushing in.)

1194
00:51:01,340 --> 00:51:03,410
Hi. Our orders are served right away!

1195
00:51:05,140 --> 00:51:07,310
Currently, in the 13-dollar price range,

1196
00:51:07,980 --> 00:51:09,780
Extraordinary Couple and HunGry's...

1197
00:51:11,150 --> 00:51:12,619
sales are the same.

1198
00:51:12,620 --> 00:51:15,889
(The sales are tied.)

1199
00:51:15,890 --> 00:51:17,820
We used every possible card we could,

1200
00:51:18,160 --> 00:51:20,930
but the announcement said the scores were the same.

1201
00:51:21,230 --> 00:51:22,329
- Are you sold out?
- No, we're not.

1202
00:51:22,330 --> 00:51:23,499
The next booth is sold out.

1203
00:51:23,500 --> 00:51:24,730
No, we still have a lot.

1204
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:26,369
It's being freshly cooked right now.

1205
00:51:26,370 --> 00:51:28,000
It's because we prepared twice as much.

1206
00:51:28,670 --> 00:51:29,870
We were smart.

1207
00:51:30,440 --> 00:51:31,639
It was our strategy.

1208
00:51:31,640 --> 00:51:34,639
We prepared gnocchi, which gave us...

1209
00:51:34,640 --> 00:51:38,139
the best efficiency within the set ingredient cost.

1210
00:51:38,140 --> 00:51:40,450
Exactly. That was the main strategy.

1211
00:51:40,680 --> 00:51:44,950
With that, we prepared about 100 portions.

1212
00:51:45,180 --> 00:51:46,720
We can't serve all of the orders.

1213
00:51:47,090 --> 00:51:48,750
Chef Kim Hee Eun is truly amazing.

1214
00:51:52,390 --> 00:51:54,860
We're doomed. Extraordinary Couple has 20 more customers.

1215
00:51:55,630 --> 00:51:56,829
Jong In, if we were to use the yakisoba's...

1216
00:51:56,830 --> 00:51:58,700
chicken and shrimp, could we make it?

1217
00:51:59,230 --> 00:52:00,269
Sorry?

1218
00:52:00,270 --> 00:52:03,100
Can we make it if we use the chicken and shrimp from the yakisoba?

1219
00:52:03,300 --> 00:52:04,539
No, it'll kill us.

1220
00:52:04,540 --> 00:52:06,310
Should we win by using the ingredients for the later rounds?

1221
00:52:06,810 --> 00:52:08,409
We could do that by using the chicken and shrimp...

1222
00:52:08,410 --> 00:52:09,439
reserved for the second half.

1223
00:52:09,440 --> 00:52:10,510
Should we keep selling?

1224
00:52:10,680 --> 00:52:12,039
- No.
- No?

1225
00:52:12,040 --> 00:52:13,980
Since it's a tie, we should sell more right now.

1226
00:52:14,550 --> 00:52:16,010
We can't serve anything.

1227
00:52:16,480 --> 00:52:17,950
We could still beat them in Round One.

1228
00:52:18,980 --> 00:52:20,049
Number 8245.

1229
00:52:20,050 --> 00:52:21,819
(Giving away the second-half orders if they use more ingredients)

1230
00:52:21,820 --> 00:52:23,989
Stop. Please stop.

1231
00:52:23,990 --> 00:52:25,359
Winning is good.

1232
00:52:25,360 --> 00:52:27,959
The problem is that we can't serve all of them.

1233
00:52:27,960 --> 00:52:29,860
We had to consider the second half.

1234
00:52:31,800 --> 00:52:33,830
(After much deliberation, Kim Hoon chose to...)

1235
00:52:33,970 --> 00:52:35,699
- Should we cut it?
- We should.

1236
00:52:35,700 --> 00:52:37,269
Right? We've got 73.

1237
00:52:37,270 --> 00:52:38,340
Please cut it.

1238
00:52:40,310 --> 00:52:42,039
(HunGry is sold out.)

1239
00:52:42,040 --> 00:52:43,180
Let's do better in Round Two.

1240
00:52:44,110 --> 00:52:46,380
- We're sold out. I'm sorry.
- Really?

1241
00:52:47,180 --> 00:52:48,480
We're selling yakisoba in the second half.

1242
00:52:49,550 --> 00:52:53,549
(The customers flock to Extraordinary Couple.)

1243
00:52:53,550 --> 00:52:55,620
Hurry, Chef.

1244
00:52:57,120 --> 00:53:01,890
(Extraordinary Couple keeps selling until the end for the decisive win.)

1245
00:53:02,630 --> 00:53:05,100
The first half of business has ended.

1246
00:53:06,670 --> 00:53:07,670
HunGry...

1247
00:53:07,671 --> 00:53:09,769
- sold 949 dollars.
- Thank you.

1248
00:53:09,770 --> 00:53:11,640
- Customer ratings, 4.1.
- Thank you. Next order, please.

1249
00:53:11,940 --> 00:53:12,969
Come over!

1250
00:53:12,970 --> 00:53:15,370
Extraordinary Couple sold 1,118 dollars.

1251
00:53:15,710 --> 00:53:17,580
Customer ratings, 4.1.

1252
00:53:18,110 --> 00:53:21,009
In the first half, Extraordinary Couple has won.

1253
00:53:21,010 --> 00:53:23,250
(Kim Hee Eun: Won, Kim Hoon: Lost)

1254
00:53:25,980 --> 00:53:28,389
The first half of business has ended.

1255
00:53:28,390 --> 00:53:30,389
(The end of the Street Beer Festival's first half)

1256
00:53:30,390 --> 00:53:31,559
(Results of the first half)

1257
00:53:31,560 --> 00:53:32,589
(Hong Seok Cheon: Won, Shin Ga Young: Lost)

1258
00:53:32,590 --> 00:53:36,730
(Kim Hee Eun: Won, Kim Hoon: Lost, Edward Kwon: Won, Lim Ki Hak: Lost)

1259
00:53:37,200 --> 00:53:39,199
We need to hurry up and deep-fry the mianbao xia.

1260
00:53:39,200 --> 00:53:40,370
Come back in.

1261
00:53:40,970 --> 00:53:42,499
- Is there more, Chef Ga Young?
- No.

1262
00:53:42,500 --> 00:53:43,700
- No?
- We're done.

1263
00:53:44,670 --> 00:53:46,470
This feels tragic.

1264
00:53:47,870 --> 00:53:49,539
It couldn't be helped.

1265
00:53:49,540 --> 00:53:50,640
- No, it couldn't.
- Right?

1266
00:53:50,980 --> 00:53:52,140
What happened has happened.

1267
00:53:52,710 --> 00:53:53,710
Let's do better in Round Two.

1268
00:53:54,050 --> 00:53:55,210
Let's do better in Round Two.

1269
00:53:56,010 --> 00:53:58,250
Break time starts now.

1270
00:53:59,320 --> 00:54:03,160
The 2nd half will start at 7:30pm.

1271
00:54:03,490 --> 00:54:04,760
- Please get ready.
- Hi.

1272
00:54:04,990 --> 00:54:06,660
I'm today's MC...

1273
00:54:06,790 --> 00:54:08,689
and comedian, Heo Kyeong Hwan.

1274
00:54:08,690 --> 00:54:09,699
Nice to meet you.

1275
00:54:09,700 --> 00:54:11,160
(MC Heo Kyeong Hwan)

1276
00:54:12,560 --> 00:54:14,630
It's currently break time, right?

1277
00:54:14,870 --> 00:54:16,300
After the break,

1278
00:54:16,600 --> 00:54:19,740
the booths will start selling their new menus.

1279
00:54:20,010 --> 00:54:21,740
How is it break time when we don't get a break?

1280
00:54:22,810 --> 00:54:23,940
I'd love to watch the performance.

1281
00:54:25,840 --> 00:54:27,379
Wait, even we can watch it.

1282
00:54:27,380 --> 00:54:29,720
We don't have time to watch it.

1283
00:54:33,490 --> 00:54:38,059
("I Don't Love You" by Urban Zakapa)

1284
00:54:38,060 --> 00:54:42,630
(There's no other reason)

1285
00:54:44,360 --> 00:54:50,599
(I don't want to say the words)

1286
00:54:50,600 --> 00:54:55,540
(I'm sorry or forgive me)

1287
00:54:57,510 --> 00:54:59,310
If the match is tied 1-1,

1288
00:54:59,880 --> 00:55:03,220
the final winner will be decided by the customer ratings.

1289
00:55:05,550 --> 00:55:06,650
Customer ratings are what matter now.

1290
00:55:07,590 --> 00:55:09,960
We would've been destroyed if not for the customer ratings.

1291
00:55:10,320 --> 00:55:12,320
It's okay. Let's get back on our feet.

1292
00:55:12,860 --> 00:55:14,030
Let's see it through.

1293
00:55:14,730 --> 00:55:15,930
We need to knock them down.

1294
00:55:18,300 --> 00:55:19,729
- They're still selling.
- What?

1295
00:55:19,730 --> 00:55:20,930
They're still selling.

1296
00:55:21,800 --> 00:55:23,240
May I know your number?

1297
00:55:23,500 --> 00:55:24,970
Who didn't get their order?

1298
00:55:25,470 --> 00:55:27,210
- Chef, we need gnocchi.
- Okay.

1299
00:55:27,710 --> 00:55:29,270
We have to fry them now.

1300
00:55:29,540 --> 00:55:30,740
Is the temperature right?

1301
00:55:30,810 --> 00:55:32,810
- We're doomed.
- No, we can do it.

1302
00:55:33,510 --> 00:55:36,380
The second half of business begins now.

1303
00:55:38,020 --> 00:55:41,490
(Around 1,400 attendees have entered.)

1304
00:55:41,950 --> 00:55:43,890
Business and cooking are very different.

1305
00:55:44,860 --> 00:55:46,930
We need to get the ramyeon ready. What now?

1306
00:55:47,290 --> 00:55:48,330
Hurry.

1307
00:55:49,160 --> 00:55:50,360
We sold too much.

1308
00:55:50,660 --> 00:55:53,130
We can't get the next menu ready. This is bad.

1309
00:55:53,930 --> 00:55:55,000
Thank you.

1310
00:55:55,600 --> 00:55:56,840
Number 2837.

1311
00:55:56,970 --> 00:55:59,840
(Extraordinary Couple is done with the first half.)

1312
00:56:00,010 --> 00:56:02,310
What now? Can we do it?

1313
00:56:03,440 --> 00:56:05,710
Let's keep going. You're deep-frying them, right?

1314
00:56:06,510 --> 00:56:08,749
In the second half, a hangover menu was needed,

1315
00:56:08,750 --> 00:56:10,280
so we chose ramyeon.

1316
00:56:10,480 --> 00:56:14,450
After my husband and I have drinks,

1317
00:56:14,820 --> 00:56:17,920
we always crave ramyeon or something with soup.

1318
00:56:18,260 --> 00:56:20,990
"What's so special about ramyeon made by chefs?"

1319
00:56:21,060 --> 00:56:24,330
"How will you make it special?"

1320
00:56:24,430 --> 00:56:25,960
We decided to add an extraordinary sauce.

1321
00:56:26,500 --> 00:56:27,999
What we prepared is...

1322
00:56:28,000 --> 00:56:30,670
a tom yum goong-style ramyeon that's refreshing and spicy.

1323
00:56:31,100 --> 00:56:32,670
It's a warm dish,

1324
00:56:32,770 --> 00:56:35,170
and together with beer, it's amazing.

1325
00:56:35,610 --> 00:56:39,339
(Specialising in hangovers, extraordinary ramyeon)

1326
00:56:39,340 --> 00:56:42,309
But who would buy a 13-dollar ramyeon?

1327
00:56:42,310 --> 00:56:45,080
The customers will find out that the ramyeon is a side dish...

1328
00:56:45,120 --> 00:56:46,849
paired with a different main menu.

1329
00:56:46,850 --> 00:56:49,549
That's our strategy. We wanted to serve a hearty meal.

1330
00:56:49,550 --> 00:56:50,720
(Extraordinary shrimp, the main menu)

1331
00:56:51,060 --> 00:56:52,320
The shrimps are red prawns...

1332
00:56:53,130 --> 00:56:55,390
and King prawns.

1333
00:56:55,530 --> 00:56:57,260
The two will be cooked differently.

1334
00:56:57,630 --> 00:56:59,730
Red prawns provide a smoky flavour.

1335
00:57:04,140 --> 00:57:07,140
(Deep-fried King prawns)

1336
00:57:10,110 --> 00:57:12,079
Crispy because they're deep-fried with rice paper.

1337
00:57:12,080 --> 00:57:13,880
It's a light-textured fritter.

1338
00:57:16,380 --> 00:57:17,619
The meal comes with...

1339
00:57:17,620 --> 00:57:21,020
extraordinary ramyeon and extraordinary shrimp.

1340
00:57:21,890 --> 00:57:25,190
Our opponent also prepared noodles.

1341
00:57:25,390 --> 00:57:27,029
"So they also came up with a noodle dish."

1342
00:57:27,030 --> 00:57:29,360
"A dish that's hearty."

1343
00:57:30,560 --> 00:57:32,760
But I couldn't understand why they chose that one.

1344
00:57:33,930 --> 00:57:36,570
(HunGry in the same 13-dollar price range)

1345
00:57:36,770 --> 00:57:38,640
We must win Round Two.

1346
00:57:39,240 --> 00:57:40,809
Cook as much as you can...

1347
00:57:40,810 --> 00:57:41,870
because customers will flood in, got it?

1348
00:57:42,270 --> 00:57:45,010
When we thought about the ultimate festival dish...

1349
00:57:45,080 --> 00:57:47,479
It was something carb-heavy you could enjoy with beer,

1350
00:57:47,480 --> 00:57:49,279
but we couldn't really think of anything.

1351
00:57:49,280 --> 00:57:51,449
We were going for a dish that goes well with beer,

1352
00:57:51,450 --> 00:57:52,820
and it was yakisoba.

1353
00:57:53,220 --> 00:57:55,920
It was the ultimate item with plenty of evidence...

1354
00:57:56,020 --> 00:57:57,789
showing how successful it had been at festivals,

1355
00:57:57,790 --> 00:57:59,489
so the menu didn't seem bad at all.

1356
00:57:59,490 --> 00:58:01,089
(HunGry's second-half menu)

1357
00:58:01,090 --> 00:58:02,789
(Prawn yakisoba with butter rice cakes)

1358
00:58:02,790 --> 00:58:04,129
I doubt people will want to buy...

1359
00:58:04,130 --> 00:58:06,630
ramyeon for 13 dollars.

1360
00:58:07,030 --> 00:58:08,469
(The first-half battle was between...)

1361
00:58:08,470 --> 00:58:09,869
(chicken skewers and sweet fried chicken.)

1362
00:58:09,870 --> 00:58:13,609
(The second half is a noodle showdown.)

1363
00:58:13,610 --> 00:58:18,040
(Hangover ramyeon versus yakisoba)

1364
00:58:18,280 --> 00:58:20,379
It'll be interesting to see which will win between...

1365
00:58:20,380 --> 00:58:21,710
a familiar taste and a dish by a Michelin chef.

1366
00:58:22,280 --> 00:58:27,190
The 2nd half of the 1-on-1 same price battle begins now.

1367
00:58:29,190 --> 00:58:30,360
I'm thirsty.

1368
00:58:32,120 --> 00:58:33,160
What's going on?

1369
00:58:33,530 --> 00:58:35,159
- What?
- Already?

1370
00:58:35,160 --> 00:58:36,229
We already got a yakisoba order.

1371
00:58:36,230 --> 00:58:37,330
They're placing orders.

1372
00:58:38,730 --> 00:58:40,370
Jong In, just cook five servings at a time, okay?

1373
00:58:40,500 --> 00:58:42,230
- Cook what?
- Yakisoba.

1374
00:58:42,930 --> 00:58:44,569
There are seriously like 30 teams...

1375
00:58:44,570 --> 00:58:45,640
waiting out there.

1376
00:58:46,300 --> 00:58:47,639
Why are they waiting in line already?

1377
00:58:47,640 --> 00:58:49,909
What? Because they saw the yakisoba sign.

1378
00:58:49,910 --> 00:58:50,910
Maybe they want to try butter rice cake.

1379
00:58:51,110 --> 00:58:52,239
This is a good thing.

1380
00:58:52,240 --> 00:58:53,480
There is no line at Chef Hee Eun's restaurant.

1381
00:58:54,380 --> 00:58:57,750
(3 minutes into the second half, outside the restaurant)

1382
00:58:59,050 --> 00:59:00,449
What? We should do this.

1383
00:59:00,450 --> 00:59:02,790
(Extraordinary Couple hasn't opened the restaurant yet.)

1384
00:59:03,020 --> 00:59:04,059
Why are there so many people?

1385
00:59:04,060 --> 00:59:05,060
(The waiting line at HunGry)

1386
00:59:05,061 --> 00:59:06,220
There are even more people than earlier.

1387
00:59:07,260 --> 00:59:08,889
Even from the break time,

1388
00:59:08,890 --> 00:59:10,929
there was already an unbelievably long line...

1389
00:59:10,930 --> 00:59:11,930
waiting for the yakisoba.

1390
00:59:12,330 --> 00:59:14,199
"If we order it again, will we get the butter rice cake again?"

1391
00:59:14,200 --> 00:59:15,470
Some people asked things like this,

1392
00:59:15,670 --> 00:59:18,569
but I think our success at night was because of the video.

1393
00:59:18,570 --> 00:59:20,839
It was too bright outside during the first half.

1394
00:59:20,840 --> 00:59:22,909
But in the second half, people started waiting in line...

1395
00:59:22,910 --> 00:59:24,540
after watching the video.

1396
00:59:24,680 --> 00:59:28,180
(The screen has a strong presence.)

1397
00:59:28,310 --> 00:59:31,320
And as it got darker, the white sign stood out even more.

1398
00:59:32,820 --> 00:59:35,589
(The sign towers above the crowd.)

1399
00:59:35,590 --> 00:59:37,159
I think people came over because our restaurant...

1400
00:59:37,160 --> 00:59:38,560
caught their eye when it got dark.

1401
00:59:39,460 --> 00:59:41,460
It's switched to prawn yakisoba.

1402
00:59:42,990 --> 00:59:44,130
It's prawn yakisoba now.

1403
00:59:46,260 --> 00:59:47,830
- Is this good?
- I like yakisoba.

1404
00:59:48,830 --> 00:59:51,099
I think everything we prepared...

1405
00:59:51,100 --> 00:59:52,170
finally worked in the second half.

1406
00:59:52,540 --> 00:59:54,670
- It was worth the money.
- Money well spent.

1407
00:59:55,870 --> 00:59:58,780
(Piling up)

1408
00:59:59,180 --> 01:00:01,880
Which one is the start, and which one is the last?

1409
01:00:05,650 --> 01:00:07,020
- Number 2401.
- Yes.

1410
01:00:07,490 --> 01:00:08,490
Thank you.

1411
01:00:09,550 --> 01:00:11,189
- Do you want the butter rice cake?
- Yes.

1412
01:00:11,190 --> 01:00:12,319
- You can take one from here.
- Okay.

1413
01:00:12,320 --> 01:00:13,890
We are running low on stock, so we can give you only one.

1414
01:00:14,430 --> 01:00:15,589
- Should I keep cooking?
- What?

1415
01:00:15,590 --> 01:00:16,830
- Keep going?
- Keep cooking.

1416
01:00:17,060 --> 01:00:19,300
We have about 32 servings to serve.

1417
01:00:19,400 --> 01:00:21,830
(HunGry got 32 orders in 15 minutes.)

1418
01:00:22,070 --> 01:00:23,600
Why isn't Chef Hee Eun coming out? That makes me afraid.

1419
01:00:24,570 --> 01:00:25,640
Why is she being so quiet?

1420
01:00:27,110 --> 01:00:28,939
We can do this.

1421
01:00:28,940 --> 01:00:30,480
(Next to them, Extraordinary Couple)

1422
01:00:30,980 --> 01:00:33,040
- Be calm and do things one by one.
- One at a time.

1423
01:00:34,410 --> 01:00:35,649
We will see you later.

1424
01:00:35,650 --> 01:00:37,920
(On standby for the opening)

1425
01:00:38,250 --> 01:00:40,850
Why are we running out of time again this time?

1426
01:00:42,120 --> 01:00:45,659
I guess we wanted to show way too many things, right?

1427
01:00:45,660 --> 01:00:46,689
(5 different tasks for the fritters, 4 different tasks for the sauces)

1428
01:00:46,690 --> 01:00:47,730
I think so.

1429
01:00:48,230 --> 01:00:49,359
(1 task for the ramyeon)

1430
01:00:49,360 --> 01:00:52,330
(It requires 10 different tasks to have 1 serving ready.)

1431
01:00:53,470 --> 01:00:55,569
Or what if we take the orders now...

1432
01:00:55,570 --> 01:00:57,199
and tell them to come back later...

1433
01:00:57,200 --> 01:00:58,799
to sober up after they're done?

1434
01:00:58,800 --> 01:01:00,769
- What did you say?
- We can just take orders now.

1435
01:01:00,770 --> 01:01:02,469
The thing is,

1436
01:01:02,470 --> 01:01:03,939
our menu is hangover ramyeon, you know.

1437
01:01:03,940 --> 01:01:05,639
So we can announce in advance...

1438
01:01:05,640 --> 01:01:06,679
that they should come back in an hour.

1439
01:01:06,680 --> 01:01:07,680
It will buy us some time to prep.

1440
01:01:07,681 --> 01:01:09,209
But it could completely ruin our business.

1441
01:01:09,210 --> 01:01:10,250
No, it wouldn't. Why would it ruin it?

1442
01:01:10,780 --> 01:01:12,319
- Somehow...
- Let's make it 30 minutes.

1443
01:01:12,320 --> 01:01:15,120
I think we should tell them to come back in 30 minutes.

1444
01:01:15,850 --> 01:01:17,759
We can have them get on the waiting list.

1445
01:01:17,760 --> 01:01:20,359
But we make them promise to come back later.

1446
01:01:20,360 --> 01:01:22,589
Our strategy was to buy some time like that,

1447
01:01:22,590 --> 01:01:24,799
get the prep done perfectly, and then serve the food...

1448
01:01:24,800 --> 01:01:25,800
all at once.

1449
01:01:26,430 --> 01:01:28,629
"We will see you at 8:15pm."

1450
01:01:28,630 --> 01:01:29,670
(If you place a pre-order now, it will be served in 30 minutes.)

1451
01:01:29,930 --> 01:01:32,399
Come back for hangover ramyeon. Promise me you will come.

1452
01:01:32,400 --> 01:01:34,910
Come back for a hangover after you're done.

1453
01:01:35,010 --> 01:01:36,269
The lines at the other places are long too.

1454
01:01:36,270 --> 01:01:37,440
- They are too long, right?
- Yes.

1455
01:01:39,640 --> 01:01:42,850
(Those who were waiting for the opening scatter away.)

1456
01:01:43,350 --> 01:01:45,520
It's not ready yet. It will be served in 40 minutes.

1457
01:01:46,350 --> 01:01:48,350
It begins at 8:15pm.

1458
01:01:49,450 --> 01:01:50,689
- Please insert the card.
- We don't have a choice here.

1459
01:01:50,690 --> 01:01:51,960
(Pre-order)

1460
01:01:52,290 --> 01:01:53,360
It's ramyeon.

1461
01:01:53,690 --> 01:01:56,390
- Do you want to eat ramyeon?
- Let's take a look.

1462
01:01:56,430 --> 01:01:58,360
- How much is it? Is it 13 dollars?
- It's 13 dollars.

1463
01:01:59,330 --> 01:02:00,770
I want some soup now.

1464
01:02:01,030 --> 01:02:02,630
- I agree.
- Right?

1465
01:02:03,130 --> 01:02:05,000
- Look at that.
- I want some hot soup.

1466
01:02:05,440 --> 01:02:07,339
Extraordinary Couple is selling ramyeon,

1467
01:02:07,340 --> 01:02:08,770
so people are waiting in line.

1468
01:02:09,510 --> 01:02:10,510
Number 8023.

1469
01:02:11,640 --> 01:02:12,740
We have 24 orders already?

1470
01:02:13,850 --> 01:02:15,880
We should take more orders a first-come, first-served basis.

1471
01:02:15,950 --> 01:02:17,120
We are doing well.

1472
01:02:17,420 --> 01:02:20,550
(The promised opening hour)

1473
01:02:20,750 --> 01:02:22,589
We should take customers now.

1474
01:02:22,590 --> 01:02:23,819
Shall we begin now?

1475
01:02:23,820 --> 01:02:25,060
- Open the restaurant?
- Yes.

1476
01:02:25,260 --> 01:02:28,189
(Shrimp chips and French fries at the bottom)

1477
01:02:28,190 --> 01:02:31,330
(Deep-fried prawn heads)

1478
01:02:31,730 --> 01:02:34,830
(Deep-fried king prawn)

1479
01:02:34,930 --> 01:02:37,240
- We don't give up.
- We never give up.

1480
01:02:37,540 --> 01:02:38,569
We don't know it yet.

1481
01:02:38,570 --> 01:02:39,970
(Red prawn covered with kataifi)

1482
01:02:40,770 --> 01:02:42,939
(Grilled lemon to cut through the greasiness)

1483
01:02:42,940 --> 01:02:44,410
The lemon sauce.

1484
01:02:45,080 --> 01:02:47,679
You can adjust the amount of water to your liking...

1485
01:02:47,680 --> 01:02:50,420
and pour the sauce into it before you eat.

1486
01:02:51,380 --> 01:02:54,320
(Customers are supposed to pour water themselves.)

1487
01:02:54,720 --> 01:02:55,919
Next.

1488
01:02:55,920 --> 01:02:57,460
- How many did you order?
- One.

1489
01:02:57,820 --> 01:02:59,120
- How many?
- One.

1490
01:02:59,820 --> 01:03:02,090
You can add the seasoning powder to this.

1491
01:03:02,360 --> 01:03:03,759
The food was good, so I came back.

1492
01:03:03,760 --> 01:03:05,199
Thank you so much.

1493
01:03:05,200 --> 01:03:06,530
Cilantro lover and scallion lover.

1494
01:03:07,070 --> 01:03:08,229
- Thank you.
- Please enjoy it...

1495
01:03:08,230 --> 01:03:09,369
- and leave us a good rating.
- Okay.

1496
01:03:09,370 --> 01:03:11,070
Enjoy your food.

1497
01:03:11,240 --> 01:03:13,940
(The orders keep rolling in.)

1498
01:03:14,670 --> 01:03:15,939
We have 30 orders to serve.

1499
01:03:15,940 --> 01:03:18,809
(12 completed, 30 pre-ordered, 42 orders in total)

1500
01:03:18,810 --> 01:03:19,880
Help me.

1501
01:03:22,710 --> 01:03:23,720
This is interesting.

1502
01:03:27,220 --> 01:03:28,550
- The prawn is good.
- Right.

1503
01:03:32,190 --> 01:03:33,290
- It's tender, isn't it?
- Yes.

1504
01:03:34,890 --> 01:03:36,290
Extraordinary Couple is good.

1505
01:03:37,760 --> 01:03:38,830
It smells tangy and refreshing.

1506
01:03:39,100 --> 01:03:40,200
It's tom yum goong.

1507
01:03:40,670 --> 01:03:41,900
I like tom yum goong.

1508
01:03:42,830 --> 01:03:44,169
(Exclaiming)

1509
01:03:44,170 --> 01:03:45,640
- Is it good?
- Yes.

1510
01:03:45,840 --> 01:03:46,870
Isn't it just a shrimp chip?

1511
01:03:47,670 --> 01:03:48,670
It's different.

1512
01:03:49,370 --> 01:03:50,940
This is the best thing I've had today.

1513
01:03:57,450 --> 01:03:58,480
This is insane.

1514
01:04:01,190 --> 01:04:02,850
It tastes like tom yum goong.

1515
01:04:03,460 --> 01:04:04,760
This is so good.

1516
01:04:06,390 --> 01:04:08,189
I want to give a shout-out to it.

1517
01:04:08,190 --> 01:04:09,360
It's incredible.

1518
01:04:11,000 --> 01:04:13,400
We can't miss out on this golden hour of sales.

1519
01:04:14,330 --> 01:04:15,669
Let's not give up until the very end.

1520
01:04:15,670 --> 01:04:17,100
Let's push for a sell-out.

1521
01:04:18,600 --> 01:04:20,070
I really don't want to lose.

1522
01:04:21,540 --> 01:04:23,810
Never. I cannot lose.

1523
01:04:24,610 --> 01:04:26,580
They have only 60 servings, so we're good.

1524
01:04:29,550 --> 01:04:32,480
They have an exact number of ramyeon packs,

1525
01:04:32,920 --> 01:04:34,050
so they can't stretch their portions.

1526
01:04:34,920 --> 01:04:36,049
All they can do is 60 servings.

1527
01:04:36,050 --> 01:04:37,260
If we sell all of this, we will win.

1528
01:04:37,460 --> 01:04:38,460
As long as the ratings are good.

1529
01:04:38,990 --> 01:04:39,990
You get it, right?

1530
01:04:39,991 --> 01:04:41,229
- Totally.
- Okay.

1531
01:04:41,230 --> 01:04:43,660
(The start of this strategy)

1532
01:04:44,230 --> 01:04:45,700
What are these cup noodles for?

1533
01:04:46,630 --> 01:04:49,029
What caught my eye earlier were the 60 ramyeon packs.

1534
01:04:49,030 --> 01:04:50,070
I found it on the list.

1535
01:04:52,470 --> 01:04:54,239
(They gave up on the first half where defeat seemed certain.)

1536
01:04:54,240 --> 01:04:55,240
Should we cut it off?

1537
01:04:55,310 --> 01:04:56,739
- I think we should.
- I know, right?

1538
01:04:56,740 --> 01:04:58,279
We have 73 orders. Cut it off.

1539
01:04:58,280 --> 01:05:00,140
(To secure the ingredients for the second half)

1540
01:05:00,710 --> 01:05:02,549
They use cup noodles, so they can't stretch the portions.

1541
01:05:02,550 --> 01:05:03,620
They can't.

1542
01:05:04,350 --> 01:05:05,350
Let's do this.

1543
01:05:05,350 --> 01:05:06,350
(Kim Hoon has already figured out the opponent's stock.)

1544
01:05:06,350 --> 01:05:07,350
Seriously, I'm going to win.

1545
01:05:08,320 --> 01:05:11,360
If we make more yakisoba with chicken and prawns...

1546
01:05:12,590 --> 01:05:14,259
and sell more than their 60 servings of ramyeon,

1547
